1
00:01:00,721 --> 00:01:04,057
<i>FLYNN: This is the story of how I died.</i>

2
00:01:05,601 --> 00:01:10,188
<i>But don't worry, this is a fun story,</i>
<i>and the truth is, it isn't even mine.</i>

3
00:01:10,273 --> 00:01:13,275
<i>This is the story of a girl</i>
<i>named Rapunzel.</i>

4
00:01:15,069 --> 00:01:16,778
<i>And it starts with the sun.</i>

5
00:01:18,656 --> 00:01:23,285
<i>Once upon a time, a single drop</i>
<i>of sunlight fell from the heavens.</i>

6
00:01:23,369 --> 00:01:29,040
<i>And from this small drop of sun</i>
<i>grew a magic golden flower.</i>

7
00:01:29,959 --> 00:01:33,170
<i>It had the ability to heal</i>
<i>the sick and injured.</i>

8
00:01:34,672 --> 00:01:38,216
<i>Oh, you see that old woman over there?</i>
<i>You might want to remember her.</i>

9
00:01:38,301 --> 00:01:39,301
<i>She's kind of important.</i>

10
00:01:41,095 --> 00:01:43,054
<i>Centuries passed</i>

11
00:01:43,139 --> 00:01:45,432
<i>and a hop, skip and a boat ride away</i>
<i>there grew a kingdom.</i>

12
00:01:46,350 --> 00:01:49,561
<i>The kingdom was ruled</i>
<i>by a beloved king and queen.</i>

13
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:53,190
<i>And the queen</i>
<i>was about to have a baby.</i>

14
00:01:53,858 --> 00:01:54,941
<i>But she got sick.</i>

15
00:01:56,027 --> 00:01:57,027
<i>Really sick.</i>

16
00:01:57,778 --> 00:01:59,070
<i>She was running out of time,</i>

17
00:01:59,155 --> 00:02:02,240
<i>and that's when people</i>
<i>start to look for a miracle.</i>

18
00:02:02,325 --> 00:02:05,660
<i>Or in this case, a magic golden flower.</i>

19
00:02:06,162 --> 00:02:08,914
<i>Ah! I told you she'd be important.</i>

20
00:02:08,998 --> 00:02:11,249
<i>Instead of sharing the sun's gift,</i>

21
00:02:11,334 --> 00:02:14,044
<i>this woman, Mother Gothel,</i>
<i>hoarded its healing power</i>

22
00:02:14,128 --> 00:02:17,422
<i>and used it to keep herself young</i>
<i>for hundreds of years.</i>

23
00:02:17,507 --> 00:02:21,009
<i>And all she had to do</i>
<i>was sing a special song.</i>

24
00:02:21,719 --> 00:02:25,388
(SINGING) Flower, gleam and glow

25
00:02:26,057 --> 00:02:29,851
<i>Let your power shine</i>

26
00:02:30,353 --> 00:02:33,605
<i>Make the clock reverse</i>

27
00:02:33,689 --> 00:02:37,526
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

28
00:02:37,610 --> 00:02:40,779
<i>What once was mine</i>

29
00:02:40,863 --> 00:02:44,699
<i>FLYNN: You get the gist. She sings to it,</i>
<i>she turns young. Creepy, right?</i>

30
00:02:44,825 --> 00:02:46,576
(VOICES APPROACHING)

31
00:02:55,836 --> 00:02:56,878
We found it!

32
00:03:03,052 --> 00:03:07,722
<i>FLYNN: The magic of the golden flower</i>
<i>healed the queen.</i>

33
00:03:08,558 --> 00:03:13,520
<i>A healthy baby girl, a princess</i>
<i>was born, with beautiful golden hair.</i>

34
00:03:13,604 --> 00:03:15,188
(BABY COOING HAPPILY)

35
00:03:15,273 --> 00:03:16,648
(CHUCKLING)

36
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:18,692
(COOING)

37
00:03:21,279 --> 00:03:22,487
(LAUGHING SOFTLY)

38
00:03:22,572 --> 00:03:25,240
<i>FLYNN: I'll give you a hint,</i>
<i>that's Rapunzel.</i>

39
00:03:25,324 --> 00:03:26,533
(GIGGLES)

40
00:03:27,201 --> 00:03:28,493
<i>To celebrate her birth,</i>

41
00:03:28,578 --> 00:03:31,871
<i>the king and queen</i>
<i>launched a flying lantern into the sky.</i>

42
00:03:31,956 --> 00:03:35,750
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

43
00:03:37,336 --> 00:03:40,547
<i>And for that one moment,</i>
<i>everything was perfect.</i>

44
00:03:43,467 --> 00:03:45,010
<i>And then that moment ended.</i>

45
00:03:46,762 --> 00:03:50,849
(SINGING) Flower, gleam and glow

46
00:03:52,810 --> 00:03:56,438
<i>Let your power shine</i>

47
00:03:56,814 --> 00:03:58,607
<i>Make the clock...</i>

48
00:03:58,774 --> 00:03:59,983
(GASPS)

49
00:04:04,405 --> 00:04:05,405
(RAPUNZEL CRYING)

50
00:04:05,489 --> 00:04:07,991
FLYNN: Gothel broke into the castle,
<i>stole the child,</i>

51
00:04:08,075 --> 00:04:10,118
<i>and just like that, gone!</i>

52
00:04:12,330 --> 00:04:15,749
<i>The kingdom searched and searched,</i>
<i>but they could not find the princess.</i>

53
00:04:16,042 --> 00:04:19,127
<i>For deep within the forest,</i>
<i>in a hidden tower,</i>

54
00:04:19,211 --> 00:04:20,712
<i>Gothel raised the child as her own.</i>

55
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:23,632
RAPUNZEL: (SINGING)
<i>Save what has been lost</i>

56
00:04:23,799 --> 00:04:27,677
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

57
00:04:27,762 --> 00:04:30,388
<i>What once was mine</i>

58
00:04:30,473 --> 00:04:33,058
FLYNN: Gothel had found
<i>her new magic flower,</i>

59
00:04:33,142 --> 00:04:35,852
<i>but this time,</i>
<i>she was determined to keep it hidden.</i>

60
00:04:36,479 --> 00:04:39,064
Why can't I go outside?

61
00:04:39,148 --> 00:04:41,775
The outside world is a dangerous place,

62
00:04:41,859 --> 00:04:44,402
filled with horrible, selfish people.

63
00:04:44,487 --> 00:04:47,572
You must stay here, where you're safe.

64
00:04:47,657 --> 00:04:49,240
Do you understand, flower?

65
00:04:49,325 --> 00:04:50,700
Yes, Mommy.

66
00:04:53,996 --> 00:04:58,541
FLYNN: But the walls ofthat tower
<i>could not hide everything.</i>

67
00:05:01,837 --> 00:05:03,296
<i>Each year, on her birthday,</i>

68
00:05:03,381 --> 00:05:06,925
<i>the king and queen released</i>
<i>thousands of lanterns into the sky</i>

69
00:05:07,009 --> 00:05:12,097
<i>in hope that one day</i>
<i>their lost princess would return.</i>

70
00:05:28,739 --> 00:05:30,073
(WHIMPERS)

71
00:05:31,075 --> 00:05:32,492
Ha!

72
00:05:33,202 --> 00:05:34,285
Hmm.

73
00:05:34,620 --> 00:05:38,123
Well, I guess
Pascal's not hiding out here.

74
00:05:38,999 --> 00:05:40,250
(SNIGGERING)

75
00:05:41,127 --> 00:05:42,335
- Gotcha!
- (SCREAMS)

76
00:05:42,712 --> 00:05:43,920
(PANTS)

77
00:05:44,046 --> 00:05:48,591
That's 22 for me.
How about 23 out of 45?

78
00:05:50,010 --> 00:05:52,137
Okay. Well, what do you want to do?

79
00:05:52,346 --> 00:05:53,638
(SQUEAKS)

80
00:05:54,932 --> 00:05:59,728
Yeah. I don't think so.
I like it in here, and so do you.

81
00:06:01,897 --> 00:06:05,233
Oh, come on, Pascal.
It's not so bad in there.

82
00:06:17,955 --> 00:06:21,458
(SINGING) Seven a.m., the usual
<i>morning lineup</i>

83
00:06:22,376 --> 00:06:26,588
<i>Start on the chores</i>
<i>And sweep till the floor's all clean</i>

84
00:06:27,089 --> 00:06:30,675
<i>Polish and wax, do laundry</i>
<i>and mop and shine up</i>

85
00:06:30,759 --> 00:06:35,180
<i>Sweep again and by then it's, like, 7:15</i>

86
00:06:35,264 --> 00:06:39,684
<i>And so I'll read a book</i>
<i>Or maybe two or three</i>

87
00:06:39,768 --> 00:06:44,022
<i>I'll add a few new paintings</i>
<i>to my gallery</i>

88
00:06:44,106 --> 00:06:48,443
<i>I'll play guitar and knit</i>
<i>and cook and basically</i>

89
00:06:48,527 --> 00:06:53,072
<i>Just wonder when will my life begin?</i>

90
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:06,628
<i>Then after lunch it's puzzles</i>
<i>and darts and baking</i>

91
00:07:06,712 --> 00:07:11,174
<i>Papier-mâché, a bit of ballet and chess</i>

92
00:07:11,509 --> 00:07:15,053
<i>Pottery and ventriloquy, candle-making</i>

93
00:07:15,137 --> 00:07:19,849
<i>Then I'll stretch, maybe sketch</i>
<i>Take a climb, sew a dress</i>

94
00:07:19,934 --> 00:07:23,895
<i>And I'll reread the books</i>
<i>If I have time to spare</i>

95
00:07:23,979 --> 00:07:28,358
<i>I'll paint the walls some more</i>
<i>I'm sure there's room somewhere</i>

96
00:07:28,442 --> 00:07:32,820
<i>And then I'll brush and brush</i>
<i>and brush and brush my hair</i>

97
00:07:32,905 --> 00:07:37,450
<i>Stuck in the same place</i>
<i>I've always been</i>

98
00:07:37,535 --> 00:07:42,580
<i>And I'll keep wondering and wondering</i>
<i>and wondering and wondering</i>

99
00:07:42,665 --> 00:07:46,042
<i>When will my life begin?</i>

100
00:07:48,003 --> 00:07:51,422
<i>Tomorrow night</i>

101
00:07:51,590 --> 00:07:55,760
<i>the lights will appear</i>

102
00:07:56,470 --> 00:07:59,722
<i>Just like they do</i>

103
00:07:59,807 --> 00:08:04,644
<i>on my birthday each year</i>

104
00:08:06,146 --> 00:08:09,440
<i>What is it like</i>

105
00:08:10,526 --> 00:08:14,445
<i>out there where they glow</i>

106
00:08:15,531 --> 00:08:19,158
<i>Now that I'm older</i>

107
00:08:19,702 --> 00:08:24,205
<i>Mother might just let me go</i>

108
00:08:47,896 --> 00:08:51,024
Wow! I could get used
to a view like this.

109
00:08:51,108 --> 00:08:52,984
Rider, come on!

110
00:08:53,068 --> 00:08:58,323
Hold on. Yep. I'm used to it.
Guys, I want a castle.

111
00:08:58,782 --> 00:09:01,618
We do this job,
you can buy your own castle.

112
00:09:11,795 --> 00:09:13,087
(SNEEZES)

113
00:09:14,006 --> 00:09:16,007
- Hay fever?
- Yeah.

114
00:09:18,010 --> 00:09:19,093
Huh?

115
00:09:19,678 --> 00:09:22,597
Wait! Hey, wait!

116
00:09:23,432 --> 00:09:26,184
Can't you picture me in a castle
of my own? Because I certainly can.

117
00:09:26,268 --> 00:09:29,145
All the things we've seen,
and it's only 8:00 in the morning!

118
00:09:29,229 --> 00:09:32,315
Gentlemen, this is a very big day!

119
00:09:32,691 --> 00:09:36,736
(SIGHS) This is it!
This is a very big day, Pascal.

120
00:09:36,820 --> 00:09:37,862
(CHUCKLES)

121
00:09:37,946 --> 00:09:40,948
I'm finally going to do it.
I'm going to ask her.

122
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:43,117
- GOTHEL: Rapunzel!
- (GASPS)

123
00:09:43,619 --> 00:09:45,286
Let down your hair!

124
00:09:46,246 --> 00:09:47,288
It's time!

125
00:09:48,582 --> 00:09:51,876
I know, I know.
Come on. Don't let her see you.

126
00:09:54,171 --> 00:09:58,174
Rapunzel!
I'm not getting any younger down here!

127
00:09:59,051 --> 00:10:00,593
Coming, Mother!

128
00:10:20,406 --> 00:10:23,658
(GRUNTING)

129
00:10:24,827 --> 00:10:27,412
(PANTING) Hi. Welcome home, Mother.

130
00:10:27,496 --> 00:10:30,748
(EXCLAIMS) Rapunzel,
how you manage to do that

131
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:34,001
every single day without fail.

132
00:10:34,086 --> 00:10:36,504
It looks absolutely exhausting, darling.

133
00:10:36,588 --> 00:10:38,965
Oh, (CHUCKLES) it's nothing.

134
00:10:39,049 --> 00:10:41,342
Then I don't know why it takes so long.

135
00:10:41,427 --> 00:10:43,845
(LAUGHS) Oh, darling, I'm just teasing.

136
00:10:44,388 --> 00:10:45,722
(CHUCKLES)

137
00:10:46,223 --> 00:10:47,348
All right.

138
00:10:47,433 --> 00:10:50,768
So, Mother, as you know
tomorrow is a very big day...

139
00:10:50,853 --> 00:10:52,437
Rapunzel, look in that mirror.

140
00:10:52,521 --> 00:10:53,980
You know what I see?

141
00:10:54,064 --> 00:10:58,151
I see a strong, confident,
beautiful young lady.

142
00:10:59,278 --> 00:11:01,446
Oh, look, you're here, too. (LAUGHS)

143
00:11:01,530 --> 00:11:04,949
I'm just teasing.
Stop taking everything so seriously.

144
00:11:05,617 --> 00:11:08,453
Okay. So, Mother,
as I was saying, tomorrow is...

145
00:11:08,537 --> 00:11:10,997
Rapunzel,
Mother's feeling a little run-down.

146
00:11:11,081 --> 00:11:14,083
Would you sing for me, dear?
Then we'll talk.

147
00:11:14,168 --> 00:11:16,502
Oh! Of course, Mother.

148
00:11:24,845 --> 00:11:26,220
(QUICKLY) Flower, gleam and glow
<i>Let your power shine</i>

149
00:11:26,305 --> 00:11:27,972
<i>Make the clock reverse</i>
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

150
00:11:28,056 --> 00:11:29,807
<i>Heal what has been hurt</i>
<i>Change the Fates' design</i>

151
00:11:29,892 --> 00:11:31,976
<i>Save what has been lost</i>
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

152
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:33,811
- Rapunzel!
- So, Mother,

153
00:11:33,896 --> 00:11:36,731
earlier I was saying tomorrow
is a big day, and you didn't respond.

154
00:11:36,815 --> 00:11:39,567
So, I'm just going to tell you,
it's my birthday! (LAUGHS)

155
00:11:39,651 --> 00:11:42,570
- Ta-da!
- No, no, no. Can't be.

156
00:11:42,654 --> 00:11:45,990
I distinctly remember.
Your birthday was last year.

157
00:11:46,074 --> 00:11:49,410
That's the funny thing about birthdays.
They're kind of an annual thing.

158
00:11:49,495 --> 00:11:50,495
(SIGHS)

159
00:11:51,246 --> 00:11:55,750
Mother, I'm turning 18,
and I wanted to ask...

160
00:11:56,210 --> 00:11:58,920
(SIGHS) What I really want
for this birthday...

161
00:11:59,046 --> 00:12:01,380
Actually what I wanted
for quite a few birthdays now...

162
00:12:01,465 --> 00:12:03,633
Rapunzel, please,
stop with the mumbling.

163
00:12:03,717 --> 00:12:06,344
You know how I feel about
the mumbling. Blah-blah-blah-blah.

164
00:12:06,428 --> 00:12:09,096
It's very annoying!
I'm just teasing. You're adorable.

165
00:12:09,181 --> 00:12:11,015
I love you so much, darling.

166
00:12:12,267 --> 00:12:13,643
(PASCAL SQUEAKS)

167
00:12:16,855 --> 00:12:18,523
(EXCLAIMS) I want to see
the floating lights.

168
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:22,318
(CHUCKLES) What?

169
00:12:22,402 --> 00:12:26,197
I was hoping you would take me
to see the floating lights.

170
00:12:26,573 --> 00:12:29,367
Oh! You mean the stars.

171
00:12:29,660 --> 00:12:30,952
That's the thing.

172
00:12:32,371 --> 00:12:35,289
I've charted stars,
and they're always constant.

173
00:12:35,374 --> 00:12:39,210
But these, they appear every year
on my birthday, Mother.

174
00:12:39,294 --> 00:12:41,254
Only on my birthday.

175
00:12:41,338 --> 00:12:46,509
And I can't help but feel like
they're meant for me.

176
00:12:47,344 --> 00:12:49,262
I need to see them, Mother.

177
00:12:49,346 --> 00:12:52,890
And not just from my window, in person.

178
00:12:52,975 --> 00:12:55,560
I have to know what they are.

179
00:12:55,644 --> 00:12:59,730
You want to go outside?
(SCOFFS) Why, Rapunzel...

180
00:13:00,357 --> 00:13:03,276
(SINGING) Look at you,
<i>as fragile as a flower</i>

181
00:13:03,986 --> 00:13:07,822
<i>Still a little sapling, just a sprout</i>

182
00:13:07,906 --> 00:13:10,741
<i>You know why we stay up in this tower</i>

183
00:13:10,826 --> 00:13:12,410
- I know, but...
- That's right.

184
00:13:12,494 --> 00:13:16,372
<i>To keep you safe and sound, dear</i>

185
00:13:16,456 --> 00:13:19,166
<i>Guess I always knew</i>
<i>this day was coming</i>

186
00:13:20,127 --> 00:13:22,837
<i>Knew that soon</i>
<i>you'd want to leave the nest</i>

187
00:13:23,505 --> 00:13:24,755
<i>Soon but not yet</i>

188
00:13:25,007 --> 00:13:27,341
<i>Shh!</i>
<i>Trust me, pet</i>

189
00:13:27,676 --> 00:13:31,512
<i>Mother knows best</i>

190
00:13:32,389 --> 00:13:33,681
(HATCH THUDDING CLOSED)

191
00:13:33,849 --> 00:13:36,934
<i>Mother knows best</i>
<i>Listen to your mother</i>

192
00:13:37,019 --> 00:13:38,019
(SCREAMS)

193
00:13:38,103 --> 00:13:39,937
<i>It's a scary world out there</i>

194
00:13:40,022 --> 00:13:41,606
<i>Mother knows best</i>

195
00:13:41,690 --> 00:13:42,648
(GRUNTING)

196
00:13:42,733 --> 00:13:44,650
<i>One way or another</i>
<i>Something will go wrong</i>

197
00:13:44,735 --> 00:13:46,402
<i>I swear</i>

198
00:13:46,486 --> 00:13:49,280
<i>Ruffians, thugs, poison ivy, quicksand</i>

199
00:13:49,364 --> 00:13:51,449
<i>Cannibals and snakes, the plague</i>

200
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:52,617
- No!
- Yes.

201
00:13:52,701 --> 00:13:55,369
<i>Also large bugs</i>
<i>Men with pointy teeth</i>

202
00:13:55,454 --> 00:13:58,873
<i>And stop! No more, you'll just upset me</i>

203
00:13:58,957 --> 00:14:01,959
<i>Mother's right here</i>
<i>Mother will protect you</i>

204
00:14:02,044 --> 00:14:05,296
<i>Darling, here's what I suggest</i>

205
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:09,550
<i>Skip the drama</i>
<i>Stay with Mama</i>

206
00:14:09,635 --> 00:14:14,430
<i>Mother knows best</i>

207
00:14:14,556 --> 00:14:15,806
(LAUGHS)

208
00:14:16,683 --> 00:14:19,477
<i>Mother knows best</i>
<i>Take it from your mumsy</i>

209
00:14:19,561 --> 00:14:22,396
<i>On your own, you won't survive</i>

210
00:14:22,481 --> 00:14:25,399
<i>Sloppy, underdressed</i>
<i>Immature, clumsy</i>

211
00:14:25,484 --> 00:14:28,319
<i>Please, they'll eat you up alive</i>

212
00:14:28,403 --> 00:14:31,572
<i>Gullible, naive</i>
<i>Positively grubby</i>

213
00:14:31,657 --> 00:14:34,408
<i>Ditsy and a bit... Well, hmm, vague</i>

214
00:14:34,493 --> 00:14:37,328
<i>Plus, I believe, getting kind of chubby</i>

215
00:14:37,412 --> 00:14:41,499
<i>I'm just saying 'cause I wuv you</i>

216
00:14:41,583 --> 00:14:44,669
<i>Mother understands</i>
<i>Mother's here to help you</i>

217
00:14:44,753 --> 00:14:50,007
<i>All I have is one request</i>

218
00:14:54,096 --> 00:14:56,722
- Rapunzel?
- Yes?

219
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:02,019
Don't ever ask to leave this tower again.

220
00:15:03,981 --> 00:15:05,272
Yes, Mother.

221
00:15:05,774 --> 00:15:06,816
Oh.

222
00:15:07,275 --> 00:15:09,527
I love you very much, dear.

223
00:15:10,237 --> 00:15:11,821
I love you more.

224
00:15:12,114 --> 00:15:14,281
I love you most.

225
00:15:15,450 --> 00:15:17,576
(SINGING) Don't forget it

226
00:15:17,661 --> 00:15:21,330
<i>You'll regret it</i>

227
00:15:21,415 --> 00:15:25,918
<i>Mother knows best</i>

228
00:15:29,965 --> 00:15:33,134
Ta-ta! I'll see you in a bit, my flower!

229
00:15:35,512 --> 00:15:36,971
I'll be here.

230
00:15:54,281 --> 00:15:55,531
(PANTING)

231
00:15:59,244 --> 00:16:00,453
(GASPS)

232
00:16:00,662 --> 00:16:01,996
Oh, no.

233
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:04,623
No, no, no, no, no.
This is bad. This is very, very bad.

234
00:16:04,708 --> 00:16:06,417
This is really bad.

235
00:16:07,836 --> 00:16:09,920
They just can't get my nose right.

236
00:16:10,005 --> 00:16:11,380
Who cares?

237
00:16:11,465 --> 00:16:14,592
It's easy for you to say.
You guys look amazing.

238
00:16:15,552 --> 00:16:19,013
(HORSES NEIGHING)

239
00:16:24,519 --> 00:16:25,811
(PANTING)

240
00:16:30,025 --> 00:16:32,860
All right. Okay.
Give me a boost and I'll pull you up.

241
00:16:34,362 --> 00:16:35,780
Give us the satchel first.

242
00:16:35,864 --> 00:16:37,073
(EXCLAIMS)

243
00:16:37,199 --> 00:16:38,407
I just...

244
00:16:38,617 --> 00:16:42,620
I can't believe that after all we've been
through together, you don't trust me?

245
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:46,165
Ouch.

246
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:52,630
(GRUNTING)

247
00:16:54,424 --> 00:16:56,092
Now help us up, pretty boy!

248
00:16:56,176 --> 00:16:59,053
Sorry, my hands are full.

249
00:17:00,055 --> 00:17:01,180
What?

250
00:17:01,848 --> 00:17:02,890
Rider!

251
00:17:04,184 --> 00:17:05,559
(EXCLAIMS)

252
00:17:09,397 --> 00:17:11,482
Retrieve that satchel at any cost!

253
00:17:11,566 --> 00:17:12,858
SOLDIERS: Yes, sir!

254
00:17:13,318 --> 00:17:14,693
(NEIGHING)

255
00:17:18,031 --> 00:17:19,281
(GRUNTS)

256
00:17:19,407 --> 00:17:20,407
(GASPS)

257
00:17:29,417 --> 00:17:31,961
We got him now, Maximus.

258
00:17:37,175 --> 00:17:38,259
(GRUNTS)

259
00:17:39,177 --> 00:17:40,261
(URGES HORSE)

260
00:17:40,345 --> 00:17:41,470
(LAUGHS)

261
00:17:43,265 --> 00:17:44,431
(SNORTS)

262
00:17:44,766 --> 00:17:47,351
(GRUNTS) Come on, fleabag! Forward!

263
00:17:49,771 --> 00:17:51,272
No. No!

264
00:17:51,690 --> 00:17:56,902
Stop it! Stop it!
Give it to me! Give me that!

265
00:18:22,929 --> 00:18:23,888
Ha!

266
00:18:23,972 --> 00:18:24,972
(CRACKING)

267
00:18:25,599 --> 00:18:27,558
(NEIGHING IN ALARM)

268
00:18:30,812 --> 00:18:31,937
- (SCREAMS)
- (NEIGHS)

269
00:18:38,904 --> 00:18:39,904
(SPITS)

270
00:18:44,117 --> 00:18:45,492
(SNIFFING)

271
00:18:58,715 --> 00:19:00,007
(EXCLAIMS)

272
00:19:00,175 --> 00:19:01,842
(MAXIMUS NEIGHING)

273
00:19:03,762 --> 00:19:04,803
(SNORTS)

274
00:19:06,473 --> 00:19:07,514
(NICKERS)

275
00:19:26,660 --> 00:19:30,955
(GRUNTING)

276
00:19:34,209 --> 00:19:35,709
(PANTING)

277
00:19:39,047 --> 00:19:40,547
Alone at last.

278
00:19:40,715 --> 00:19:42,007
(CLANGING)

279
00:19:43,260 --> 00:19:44,551
(SQUEALS)

280
00:20:24,926 --> 00:20:25,926
Huh.

281
00:20:31,808 --> 00:20:33,309
(GASPS SOFTLY)

282
00:20:42,193 --> 00:20:43,319
- Huh?
- (GASPS)

283
00:20:43,403 --> 00:20:45,529
(CLANGING)

284
00:20:46,990 --> 00:20:49,950
(GRUNTING)

285
00:20:50,327 --> 00:20:51,618
(PANTING)

286
00:20:53,079 --> 00:20:54,747
(GRUNTING)

287
00:20:54,831 --> 00:20:55,831
(EXCLAIMS)

288
00:21:01,338 --> 00:21:02,421
Hmm.

289
00:21:04,382 --> 00:21:05,716
(CHUCKLING CONTENTEDLY)

290
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:06,800
(SQUEALS)

291
00:21:06,968 --> 00:21:09,303
(GRUNTING)

292
00:21:11,681 --> 00:21:12,681
Huh?

293
00:21:16,144 --> 00:21:19,438
Okay, okay, okay.
I've got a person in my closet.

294
00:21:19,522 --> 00:21:22,107
I've got a person in my closet.

295
00:21:23,360 --> 00:21:27,196
(ENUNCIATING)
I've got a person in my closet!

296
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:28,614
(CHUCKLES)

297
00:21:29,866 --> 00:21:32,451
Too weak to handle myself out there,
huh, Mother?

298
00:21:32,535 --> 00:21:35,662
Well, tell that to my frying pan.

299
00:21:36,164 --> 00:21:37,498
(GROANS)

300
00:21:37,999 --> 00:21:38,999
Huh?

301
00:21:49,219 --> 00:21:50,260
Hmm.

302
00:21:57,894 --> 00:21:58,894
Hmm.

303
00:22:17,205 --> 00:22:18,914
- GOTHEL: Rapunzel!
- (GASPS) Oh!

304
00:22:20,583 --> 00:22:22,418
Let down your hair!

305
00:22:22,961 --> 00:22:24,336
One moment, Mother!

306
00:22:24,421 --> 00:22:26,463
I have a big surprise!

307
00:22:26,548 --> 00:22:28,841
Uh... I do, too!

308
00:22:28,925 --> 00:22:31,260
Ooh, I bet my surprise is bigger!

309
00:22:31,553 --> 00:22:33,929
(SOFTLY) I seriously doubt it.

310
00:22:35,265 --> 00:22:38,684
I brought back parsnips. I'm going
to make hazelnut soup for dinner.

311
00:22:38,768 --> 00:22:41,145
Your favorite. Surprise!

312
00:22:41,229 --> 00:22:43,647
Well, Mother,
there's something I want to tell you.

313
00:22:43,731 --> 00:22:46,567
Oh, Rapunzel, you know I hate
leaving you after a fight.

314
00:22:46,651 --> 00:22:49,111
Especially when I've done
absolutely nothing wrong.

315
00:22:49,195 --> 00:22:51,530
I've been thinking a lot
about what you said earlier.

316
00:22:51,614 --> 00:22:54,158
I hope you're not still talking
about the stars.

317
00:22:54,242 --> 00:22:56,660
"Floating lights,"
and, yes, I'm leading up to that.

318
00:22:56,744 --> 00:22:59,246
Because I really thought
we dropped the issue, sweetheart.

319
00:22:59,330 --> 00:23:01,415
No, Mother, I'm just saying,

320
00:23:01,499 --> 00:23:04,001
you think I'm not strong enough
to handle myself out there.

321
00:23:04,085 --> 00:23:07,337
Oh, I know you're not strong enough
to handle yourself out there.

322
00:23:07,422 --> 00:23:10,674
- But if you just...
- We're done talking about this.

323
00:23:10,758 --> 00:23:13,302
- Trust me! I know what I'm...
- Rapunzel.

324
00:23:13,386 --> 00:23:15,929
- Oh, come on!
- Enough with the lights!

325
00:23:16,014 --> 00:23:20,434
You are not leaving this tower! Ever!

326
00:23:25,982 --> 00:23:30,444
(GROANS) Great. Now I'm the bad guy.

327
00:23:42,916 --> 00:23:45,792
All I was going to say, Mother, is that...

328
00:23:46,503 --> 00:23:49,213
I know what I want for my birthday now.

329
00:23:49,297 --> 00:23:51,298
And what is that?

330
00:23:51,716 --> 00:23:53,050
New paint.

331
00:23:53,718 --> 00:23:57,054
The paint made from the white shells
you once brought me.

332
00:23:57,138 --> 00:24:02,309
That is a very long trip, Rapunzel.
Almost three days' time.

333
00:24:02,560 --> 00:24:07,648
I just thought it was a better idea
than the stars.

334
00:24:09,317 --> 00:24:10,484
(SIGHS)

335
00:24:11,778 --> 00:24:14,112
You'll be all right on your own?

336
00:24:14,948 --> 00:24:17,658
I know I'm safe as long as I'm here.

337
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:28,168
GOTHEL: I'll be back
<i>in three days' time.</i>

338
00:24:29,128 --> 00:24:31,380
<i>I love you very much, dear.</i>

339
00:24:32,340 --> 00:24:33,674
RAPUNZEL: I love you more.

340
00:24:34,676 --> 00:24:36,843
GOTHEL: I love you most.

341
00:24:54,988 --> 00:24:57,322
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

342
00:24:57,532 --> 00:24:58,532
Okay.

343
00:25:14,799 --> 00:25:16,049
Huh.

344
00:25:28,813 --> 00:25:30,230
(SQUEAKING)

345
00:25:36,237 --> 00:25:37,487
(EXCLAIMS)

346
00:25:37,572 --> 00:25:38,697
Huh? What...

347
00:25:40,450 --> 00:25:41,825
(GRUNTING)

348
00:25:44,454 --> 00:25:47,205
FLYNN: Is this hair?

349
00:25:47,915 --> 00:25:51,126
Struggling... Struggling is pointless.

350
00:25:51,210 --> 00:25:52,252
Huh?

351
00:25:52,420 --> 00:25:54,129
(RAPUNZEL CLAMBERING DOWN)

352
00:25:54,672 --> 00:25:59,259
I know why you're here,
and I'm not afraid of you.

353
00:25:59,719 --> 00:26:01,261
What?

354
00:26:09,604 --> 00:26:13,482
Who are you?
And how did you find me?

355
00:26:14,442 --> 00:26:15,692
(STAMMERING SOFTLY)

356
00:26:16,944 --> 00:26:20,280
(ENUNCIATING) Who are you,
and how did you find me?

357
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:23,617
(CLEARS THROAT)

358
00:26:23,701 --> 00:26:27,788
I know not who you are,
nor how I came to find you.

359
00:26:27,872 --> 00:26:29,790
But may I just say...

360
00:26:31,125 --> 00:26:32,876
Hi.

361
00:26:35,129 --> 00:26:37,839
How you doing?
The name's Flynn Rider.

362
00:26:39,425 --> 00:26:41,218
How's your day going? Huh?

363
00:26:41,302 --> 00:26:42,344
(GRUNTS IN CONFUSION)

364
00:26:42,637 --> 00:26:46,306
Who else knows my location,
Flynn Rider?

365
00:26:46,391 --> 00:26:48,517
- All right, blondie.
- Rapunzel.

366
00:26:48,601 --> 00:26:50,268
Gesundheit. Here's the deal.

367
00:26:50,353 --> 00:26:53,230
I was in a situation,
gallivanting through the forest.

368
00:26:53,314 --> 00:26:55,607
I came across your tower and...

369
00:26:55,692 --> 00:26:56,983
Oh! Oh, no.

370
00:26:57,151 --> 00:26:58,360
Where is my satchel?

371
00:26:58,653 --> 00:27:01,863
I've hidden it.
Somewhere you'll never find it.

372
00:27:04,826 --> 00:27:06,660
It's in that pot, isn't it?

373
00:27:07,370 --> 00:27:08,704
(CLANGING)

374
00:27:09,038 --> 00:27:11,039
(GROANING)

375
00:27:11,374 --> 00:27:12,582
Huh?

376
00:27:12,875 --> 00:27:15,293
(EXCLAIMS) Would you stop that?

377
00:27:15,378 --> 00:27:18,255
Now it's hidden
where you'll never find it.

378
00:27:19,090 --> 00:27:23,093
So, what do you want with my hair?
To cut it?

379
00:27:23,177 --> 00:27:24,428
- What?
- Sell it?

380
00:27:24,512 --> 00:27:28,181
No! Listen, the only thing
I want to do with your hair

381
00:27:28,266 --> 00:27:30,600
is to get out of it, literally.

382
00:27:30,685 --> 00:27:31,768
You...

383
00:27:31,853 --> 00:27:34,479
Wait. You don't want my hair?

384
00:27:34,564 --> 00:27:36,523
Why on earth would I want your hair?

385
00:27:36,607 --> 00:27:39,234
Look, I was being chased,
I saw a tower, I climbed it.

386
00:27:39,318 --> 00:27:40,318
End of story.

387
00:27:40,403 --> 00:27:41,903
(STAMMERING) You're telling the truth?

388
00:27:42,029 --> 00:27:43,321
Yes!

389
00:27:43,531 --> 00:27:44,614
Hmm.

390
00:27:46,451 --> 00:27:49,035
(GROWLING)

391
00:27:52,206 --> 00:27:53,707
(GROWLING)

392
00:27:55,585 --> 00:27:56,626
(SQUEAKING)

393
00:27:56,711 --> 00:27:58,587
(WHISPERING) I know.
I need someone to take me.

394
00:27:58,671 --> 00:28:01,173
- (SQUEAKING)
- I think he's telling the truth, too.

395
00:28:01,257 --> 00:28:04,426
He doesn't have fangs.
But what choice do I have?

396
00:28:05,094 --> 00:28:06,219
(SIGHS)

397
00:28:06,304 --> 00:28:10,307
Okay, Flynn Rider,
I'm prepared to offer you a deal.

398
00:28:10,391 --> 00:28:12,184
- Deal?
- Look this way.

399
00:28:12,268 --> 00:28:13,643
(EXCLAIMING)

400
00:28:13,728 --> 00:28:16,605
Do you know what these are?

401
00:28:16,689 --> 00:28:19,816
You mean the lantern thing
they do for the princess?

402
00:28:20,401 --> 00:28:23,820
Lanterns? I knew they weren't stars.

403
00:28:24,906 --> 00:28:27,240
Well, tomorrow evening,

404
00:28:27,325 --> 00:28:31,203
they will light the night sky
with these lanterns.

405
00:28:31,287 --> 00:28:34,873
You will act as my guide,
take me to these lanterns,

406
00:28:34,957 --> 00:28:36,541
and return me home safely.

407
00:28:36,626 --> 00:28:40,962
Then, and only then,
will I return your satchel to you.

408
00:28:41,047 --> 00:28:42,255
That is my deal.

409
00:28:42,340 --> 00:28:43,507
Yeah.

410
00:28:43,591 --> 00:28:44,633
(GRUNTING)

411
00:28:44,717 --> 00:28:46,176
No can do.

412
00:28:46,260 --> 00:28:50,055
Unfortunately the kingdom and I
aren't exactly simpatico at the moment,

413
00:28:50,139 --> 00:28:52,432
so I won't be taking you anywhere.

414
00:28:59,023 --> 00:29:02,192
Something brought you here,
Flynn Rider.

415
00:29:02,276 --> 00:29:03,693
Call it what you will,

416
00:29:03,778 --> 00:29:06,613
- fate, destiny...
- A horse.

417
00:29:06,697 --> 00:29:09,032
So I have made the decision
to trust you.

418
00:29:09,116 --> 00:29:10,158
A horrible decision, really.

419
00:29:10,243 --> 00:29:13,328
But trust me when I tell you this.

420
00:29:15,289 --> 00:29:18,750
You can tear this tower apart
brick by brick,

421
00:29:18,835 --> 00:29:23,588
but without my help, you will never find
your precious satchel.

422
00:29:23,673 --> 00:29:25,048
(CLEARS THROAT)

423
00:29:25,132 --> 00:29:26,466
Let me get this straight.

424
00:29:26,551 --> 00:29:29,761
I take you to see the lanterns,
bring you back home,

425
00:29:29,846 --> 00:29:31,721
and you'll give me back my satchel?

426
00:29:31,806 --> 00:29:33,306
I promise.

427
00:29:35,142 --> 00:29:39,855
And when I promise something,
I never, ever break that promise.

428
00:29:42,233 --> 00:29:44,234
- Ever.
- (SQUEAKS IN AGREEMENT)

429
00:29:46,863 --> 00:29:49,239
All right, listen.
I didn't want to have to do this,

430
00:29:49,323 --> 00:29:51,074
but you leave me no choice.

431
00:29:51,826 --> 00:29:53,702
Here comes the smolder.

432
00:30:01,252 --> 00:30:05,255
This is kind of an off day for me.
This doesn't normally happen.

433
00:30:05,339 --> 00:30:07,132
Fine! I'll take you to see the lanterns.

434
00:30:07,216 --> 00:30:08,592
Really?

435
00:30:09,594 --> 00:30:10,594
Oops.

436
00:30:10,678 --> 00:30:12,679
(GASPING) You broke my smolder.

437
00:30:13,514 --> 00:30:16,766
(GRUNTING)

438
00:30:18,185 --> 00:30:20,186
Are you coming, blondie?

439
00:30:30,072 --> 00:30:33,783
(SINGING) Look at the world so close
<i>And I'm halfway to it</i>

440
00:30:35,036 --> 00:30:39,122
<i>Look at it all so big</i>
<i>Do I even dare</i>

441
00:30:40,041 --> 00:30:43,919
<i>Look at me, there at last</i>
<i>I just have to do it</i>

442
00:30:44,587 --> 00:30:48,715
<i>Should I? No</i>
<i>Here I go</i>

443
00:30:50,301 --> 00:30:51,301
(GRUNTS)

444
00:30:51,385 --> 00:30:52,761
(CHUCKLES)

445
00:30:57,808 --> 00:31:01,394
(LAUGHING)

446
00:31:15,826 --> 00:31:18,203
(LAUGHING)

447
00:31:19,622 --> 00:31:25,210
<i>Just smell the grass, the dirt</i>
<i>Just like I dreamed they'd be</i>

448
00:31:26,629 --> 00:31:31,967
<i>Just feel that summer breeze</i>
<i>The way it's calling me</i>

449
00:31:32,176 --> 00:31:33,301
(GASPS)

450
00:31:33,636 --> 00:31:38,974
<i>For, like, the first time ever</i>
<i>I'm completely free</i>

451
00:31:40,393 --> 00:31:44,270
<i>I could go running and racing</i>

452
00:31:44,355 --> 00:31:46,272
<i>And dancing and chasing</i>

453
00:31:46,565 --> 00:31:50,360
<i>And leaping and bounding</i>
<i>Hair flying, heart pounding</i>

454
00:31:50,444 --> 00:31:54,614
<i>And splashing and reeling</i>
<i>and finally feeling</i>

455
00:31:55,574 --> 00:32:01,663
<i>That's when my life begins</i>

456
00:32:09,130 --> 00:32:12,132
I can't believe I did this!

457
00:32:12,216 --> 00:32:14,509
(GASPS) I can't believe I did this.

458
00:32:14,593 --> 00:32:17,303
(LAUGHING) I can't believe I did this!

459
00:32:18,931 --> 00:32:20,765
Mother would be so furious.

460
00:32:20,850 --> 00:32:24,227
But that's okay. What she doesn't know
won't kill her, right?

461
00:32:24,311 --> 00:32:27,105
(CRYING) Oh, my gosh!
This would kill her.

462
00:32:27,273 --> 00:32:30,525
This is so fun!

463
00:32:30,985 --> 00:32:33,862
I am a horrible daughter.
I'm going back.

464
00:32:34,238 --> 00:32:36,573
(LAUGHING) I am never going back!

465
00:32:38,034 --> 00:32:40,744
I am a despicable human being!

466
00:32:40,911 --> 00:32:42,287
(WHOOPING)

467
00:32:42,955 --> 00:32:45,373
Best day ever!

468
00:32:48,377 --> 00:32:50,128
(CRYING)

469
00:32:52,006 --> 00:32:53,173
(CLEARS THROAT)

470
00:32:54,467 --> 00:32:57,886
You know,
I can't help but notice you seem

471
00:32:57,970 --> 00:33:00,513
a little at war with yourself here.

472
00:33:01,348 --> 00:33:03,933
- What?
- I'm only picking up bits and pieces.

473
00:33:04,018 --> 00:33:07,687
Overprotective mother,
forbidden road trip. This is serious stuff.

474
00:33:08,314 --> 00:33:11,399
But let me ease your conscience.
This is part of growing up.

475
00:33:11,484 --> 00:33:15,695
A little rebellion, a little adventure,
that's good. Healthy, even.

476
00:33:17,281 --> 00:33:18,698
(CHUCKLES) You think?

477
00:33:18,783 --> 00:33:21,951
I know. You're way over-thinking this,
trust me.

478
00:33:22,036 --> 00:33:24,079
Does your mother deserve it? No.

479
00:33:24,163 --> 00:33:27,082
Would this break her heart
and crush her soul? Of course.

480
00:33:27,166 --> 00:33:29,250
But you've got to do it.

481
00:33:30,086 --> 00:33:31,628
"Break her heart"?

482
00:33:32,088 --> 00:33:34,714
- In half.
- "Crush her soul"?

483
00:33:35,716 --> 00:33:36,925
Like a grape.

484
00:33:37,009 --> 00:33:40,011
She would be heartbroken. You're right.

485
00:33:40,096 --> 00:33:43,640
I am, aren't I? Oh, bother.

486
00:33:44,308 --> 00:33:48,686
All right. I can't believe I'm saying this,
but I'm letting you out of the deal.

487
00:33:48,771 --> 00:33:51,815
- What?
- That's right, but don't thank me.

488
00:33:51,899 --> 00:33:55,110
Let's turn around and get you home.
Here's your pan, here's your frog.

489
00:33:55,194 --> 00:33:56,444
I get back my satchel,

490
00:33:56,529 --> 00:33:59,864
you get back a mother-daughter
relationship based on mutual trust,

491
00:33:59,949 --> 00:34:03,159
and voilà,
we part ways as unlikely friends.

492
00:34:03,244 --> 00:34:06,287
No. I am seeing those lanterns.

493
00:34:06,372 --> 00:34:09,999
Oh, come on! What is it going to take
for me to get my satchel back?

494
00:34:10,084 --> 00:34:11,626
I will use this.

495
00:34:11,710 --> 00:34:12,710
- (TWIG SNAPPING)
- (PASCAL SQUEALS)

496
00:34:14,797 --> 00:34:17,966
(GASPS) Is it ruffians? Thugs?
Have they come for me?

497
00:34:22,054 --> 00:34:24,681
Stay calm. It can probably smell fear.

498
00:34:24,932 --> 00:34:26,307
Oh! (CHUCKLES)

499
00:34:26,517 --> 00:34:30,687
Sorry. Guess I'm just a little bit jumpy.

500
00:34:31,564 --> 00:34:35,483
Probably be best if we avoid ruffians
and thugs, though.

501
00:34:35,609 --> 00:34:38,778
(CHUCKLES SELF-CONSCIOUSLY)
Yeah, that would probably be best.

502
00:34:40,322 --> 00:34:42,866
Are you hungry?
I know a great place for lunch.

503
00:34:42,950 --> 00:34:45,201
(CHUCKLES) Where?

504
00:34:45,286 --> 00:34:47,954
Oh, don't you worry.
You'll know it when you smell it.

505
00:34:48,455 --> 00:34:51,457
(SNIFFING)

506
00:34:51,542 --> 00:34:52,584
(GRUNTS)

507
00:34:56,881 --> 00:34:59,340
(GROWLING)

508
00:35:03,178 --> 00:35:04,470
(NEIGHS)

509
00:35:05,931 --> 00:35:07,348
(TWIG SNAPS)

510
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,564
(GRUNTS)

511
00:35:15,149 --> 00:35:16,232
(CHUCKLING SOFTLY)

512
00:35:16,317 --> 00:35:19,360
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

513
00:35:19,445 --> 00:35:21,070
(NEIGHING MENACINGLY)

514
00:35:21,322 --> 00:35:22,322
(GASPS)

515
00:35:24,158 --> 00:35:25,408
(EXHALES)

516
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:27,869
A palace horse.

517
00:35:29,079 --> 00:35:30,830
Where's your rider?

518
00:35:31,457 --> 00:35:32,749
Rapunzel.

519
00:35:33,667 --> 00:35:35,001
Rapunzel!

520
00:35:35,419 --> 00:35:36,961
(NEIGHS IN CONFUSION)

521
00:35:42,426 --> 00:35:46,095
Rapunzel! Let down your hair!

522
00:35:48,015 --> 00:35:49,515
Rapunzel?

523
00:35:53,562 --> 00:35:55,855
(PANTING)

524
00:35:56,315 --> 00:35:59,400
(GRUNTING)

525
00:36:01,654 --> 00:36:04,447
(POUNDING)

526
00:36:09,370 --> 00:36:10,370
Rapunzel?

527
00:36:13,499 --> 00:36:14,707
Rapunzel!

528
00:36:29,723 --> 00:36:30,890
(GASPS)

529
00:36:39,525 --> 00:36:40,566
(GASPS)

530
00:36:59,586 --> 00:37:02,880
I know it's around here somewhere.

531
00:37:03,632 --> 00:37:07,176
Ah, there it is! The Snuggly Duckling.

532
00:37:07,261 --> 00:37:08,678
Don't worry. Very quaint place.
Perfect for you.

533
00:37:10,264 --> 00:37:13,558
Don't want you scaring and giving up
on this whole endeavor now, do we?

534
00:37:13,642 --> 00:37:17,103
- Well, I do like ducklings.
- Yay!

535
00:37:17,187 --> 00:37:18,271
(MEN CHATTERING)

536
00:37:18,731 --> 00:37:21,023
Garçon, your finest table, please!

537
00:37:21,108 --> 00:37:22,150
(GASPS)

538
00:37:27,906 --> 00:37:31,200
You smell that? Take a deep breath
through the nose. (INHALES DEEPLY)

539
00:37:31,493 --> 00:37:33,828
Really let that seep in.
What are you getting?

540
00:37:33,912 --> 00:37:37,623
To me, it's part man-smell and the other
part is really bad man-smell.

541
00:37:37,708 --> 00:37:39,709
I don't know why,
but overall it smells like the color brown.

542
00:37:39,793 --> 00:37:40,793
- Your thoughts?
- (GASPS)

543
00:37:41,962 --> 00:37:44,338
That's a lot of hair.

544
00:37:44,423 --> 00:37:46,758
She's growing it out.
Is that blood in your mustache?

545
00:37:46,842 --> 00:37:49,510
Goldie, look at all the blood
in his mustache!

546
00:37:49,803 --> 00:37:51,554
Good sir, that's a lot of blood!

547
00:37:51,638 --> 00:37:52,722
(GROWLS)

548
00:37:52,806 --> 00:37:57,393
You don't look so good, blondie. Maybe
we should get you home, call it a day.

549
00:37:57,478 --> 00:38:00,396
Probably better off.
This is a five-star joint.

550
00:38:00,481 --> 00:38:03,691
If you can't handle this place, maybe
you should be back in your tower.

551
00:38:04,151 --> 00:38:06,486
- (RAPUNZEL GASPS)
- Is this you?

552
00:38:09,490 --> 00:38:11,324
FLYNN: (GRUNTS)
Now they're just being mean.

553
00:38:11,825 --> 00:38:12,784
(CHUCKLES) It's him, all right.

554
00:38:12,868 --> 00:38:15,495
Greno, go find some guards.

555
00:38:15,579 --> 00:38:18,956
That reward
is going to buy me a new hook.

556
00:38:19,041 --> 00:38:22,502
- I could use the money.
- What about me? I'm broke!

557
00:38:22,586 --> 00:38:23,586
Get back!

558
00:38:23,837 --> 00:38:24,962
- Mine!
- Ruffians, stop!

559
00:38:25,047 --> 00:38:27,924
- We can work this out!
- Hey! Leave him alone!

560
00:38:28,008 --> 00:38:29,217
Gentlemen, please!

561
00:38:29,301 --> 00:38:32,678
Give me back my guide! Ruffians!

562
00:38:33,430 --> 00:38:35,014
(EXCLAIMING)

563
00:38:37,309 --> 00:38:38,351
(GRUNTS)

564
00:38:38,435 --> 00:38:40,228
(EXCLAIMING)

565
00:38:41,063 --> 00:38:42,605
Not the nose! Not the nose!

566
00:38:45,651 --> 00:38:47,401
Put him down!

567
00:38:50,197 --> 00:38:54,116
I don't know where I am, and I need him
to take me to see the lanterns

568
00:38:54,201 --> 00:38:57,119
because I've been dreaming about them
my entire life!

569
00:38:57,204 --> 00:39:02,166
Find your humanity!
Haven't any of you ever had a dream?

570
00:39:14,054 --> 00:39:16,889
I had a dream once.

571
00:39:19,518 --> 00:39:23,521
(PLAYING NERVOUSLY)

572
00:39:25,566 --> 00:39:27,984
(SINGING) I'm malicious, mean
<i>and scary</i>

573
00:39:28,068 --> 00:39:30,278
<i>My sneer could curdle dairy</i>

574
00:39:30,362 --> 00:39:33,823
<i>And violence-wise</i>
<i>my hands are not the cleanest</i>

575
00:39:33,907 --> 00:39:38,119
<i>But despite my evil look</i>
<i>And my temper and my hook</i>

576
00:39:38,662 --> 00:39:41,330
<i>I've always yearned</i>
<i>to be a concert pianist</i>

577
00:39:41,415 --> 00:39:42,665
(PLAYING PIANO)

578
00:39:42,749 --> 00:39:45,960
<i>Can't you see me on the stage</i>
<i>performing Mozart</i>

579
00:39:46,044 --> 00:39:49,171
<i>Tickling the ivories till they gleam</i>

580
00:39:49,256 --> 00:39:53,175
<i>Yep, I'd rather be called deadly</i>
<i>For my killer show tune medley</i>

581
00:39:54,177 --> 00:39:55,177
Thank you!

582
00:39:55,262 --> 00:39:58,014
<i>'Cause way down deep inside</i>
<i>I've got a dream</i>

583
00:39:58,098 --> 00:40:01,475
ALL: He's got a dream
<i>He's got a dream</i>

584
00:40:01,560 --> 00:40:05,521
<i>See, I ain't as cruel and vicious</i>
<i>as I seem</i>

585
00:40:05,606 --> 00:40:09,275
<i>Though I do like breaking femurs</i>
<i>You can count me with the dreamers</i>

586
00:40:09,359 --> 00:40:12,194
<i>Like everybody else I've got a dream</i>

587
00:40:12,279 --> 00:40:17,992
(MEN HUMMING DISTANTLY)

588
00:40:18,076 --> 00:40:21,829
<i>I've got scars and lumps and bruises</i>
<i>Plus something here that oozes</i>

589
00:40:21,914 --> 00:40:25,041
<i>And let's not even mention</i>
<i>my complexion</i>

590
00:40:25,125 --> 00:40:28,920
<i>But despite my extra toes</i>
<i>And my goiter and my nose</i>

591
00:40:29,004 --> 00:40:32,298
<i>I really want to make a love connection</i>

592
00:40:32,382 --> 00:40:36,093
<i>Can't you see me</i>
<i>with a special little lady?</i>

593
00:40:36,178 --> 00:40:39,513
<i>Rowing in a rowboat down the stream</i>

594
00:40:39,598 --> 00:40:43,392
<i>Though I'm one disgusting blighter</i>
<i>I'm a lover not a fighter</i>

595
00:40:43,477 --> 00:40:46,395
<i>'Cause way down deep inside</i>
<i>I've got a dream</i>

596
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:48,314
<i>- I've got a dream</i>
- ALL: He's got a dream

597
00:40:48,398 --> 00:40:50,316
<i>- I've got a dream</i>
<i>- He's got a dream</i>

598
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:53,736
<i>And I know one day</i>
<i>romance will reign supreme</i>

599
00:40:53,820 --> 00:40:55,738
<i>Though my face</i>
<i>leaves people screaming</i>

600
00:40:55,822 --> 00:40:57,740
<i>There's a child behind it dreaming</i>

601
00:40:57,824 --> 00:41:00,993
<i>Like everybody else, I've got a dream</i>

602
00:41:01,495 --> 00:41:04,664
<i>Thor would like to quit and be a florist</i>

603
00:41:05,082 --> 00:41:08,334
<i>Gunther does interior design</i>

604
00:41:08,418 --> 00:41:12,004
<i>- Ulf is into mime</i>
<i>- Attila's cupcakes are sublime</i>

605
00:41:12,089 --> 00:41:15,549
<i>Bruiser knits, Killer sews</i>
<i>Fang does little puppet shows</i>

606
00:41:15,634 --> 00:41:21,222
<i>And Vladimir collects ceramic unicorns</i>

607
00:41:21,306 --> 00:41:22,348
(DINGING)

608
00:41:22,516 --> 00:41:24,850
- What about you?
- I'm sorry, me?

609
00:41:24,935 --> 00:41:26,185
What's your dream?

610
00:41:26,269 --> 00:41:29,188
No, no, no. Sorry, boys. I don't sing.

611
00:41:30,440 --> 00:41:32,441
(SINGING) I have dreams like you
<i>No, really</i>

612
00:41:32,526 --> 00:41:34,110
<i>Just much less touchy-feely</i>

613
00:41:34,194 --> 00:41:37,238
<i>They mainly happen</i>
<i>somewhere warm and sunny</i>

614
00:41:37,322 --> 00:41:40,950
<i>On an island that I own</i>
<i>Tanned and rested and alone</i>

615
00:41:42,035 --> 00:41:44,996
<i>Surrounded by enormous</i>
<i>piles of money</i>

616
00:41:45,080 --> 00:41:46,956
<i>- I've got a dream</i>
- ALL: She's got a dream

617
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:48,791
<i>- I've got a dream</i>
<i>- She's got a dream</i>

618
00:41:48,875 --> 00:41:51,377
<i>I just want to see</i>
<i>the floating lanterns gleam</i>

619
00:41:51,461 --> 00:41:52,503
(ALL CHEERING)

620
00:41:52,587 --> 00:41:56,590
<i>And with every passing hour</i>
<i>I'm so glad I left my tower</i>

621
00:41:56,675 --> 00:41:59,510
<i>Like all you lovely folks</i>
<i>I've got a dream</i>

622
00:41:59,594 --> 00:42:01,303
<i>She's got a dream</i>
<i>He's got a dream</i>

623
00:42:01,388 --> 00:42:03,222
<i>They've got a dream</i>
<i>We've got a dream</i>

624
00:42:03,306 --> 00:42:06,517
<i>So our differences</i>
<i>ain't really that extreme</i>

625
00:42:06,601 --> 00:42:10,688
<i>We're one big team</i>

626
00:42:11,398 --> 00:42:12,606
<i>- Call us brutal</i>
<i>- Sick</i>

627
00:42:12,691 --> 00:42:15,151
<i>- Sadistic</i>
<i>- And grotesquely optimistic</i>

628
00:42:15,235 --> 00:42:17,486
<i>'Cause way down deep inside</i>
<i>we've got a dream</i>

629
00:42:17,571 --> 00:42:20,406
<i>- I've got a dream</i>
<i>- I've got a dream</i>

630
00:42:22,617 --> 00:42:23,659
(EXCLAIMING)

631
00:42:23,744 --> 00:42:29,248
<i>Yes, way down deep inside</i>
<i>I've got a dream</i>

632
00:42:34,087 --> 00:42:35,629
(ALL CHEERING)

633
00:42:37,841 --> 00:42:39,175
I found the guards!

634
00:42:41,928 --> 00:42:43,929
Where's Rider? Where is he?

635
00:42:44,389 --> 00:42:46,515
I know he's in here somewhere.
Find him.

636
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:48,642
Turn the place upside down
if you have to!

637
00:42:54,399 --> 00:42:55,399
(GASPS)

638
00:42:59,571 --> 00:43:00,696
(CHAINS RATTLING)

639
00:43:05,202 --> 00:43:07,286
Go. Live your dream.

640
00:43:08,121 --> 00:43:10,206
- I will.
- Your dream stinks.

641
00:43:10,290 --> 00:43:12,083
I was talking to her.

642
00:43:13,794 --> 00:43:15,711
Thanks for everything.

643
00:43:19,216 --> 00:43:21,884
I believe
this is the man you're looking for.

644
00:43:21,968 --> 00:43:23,844
(SLURRING) You got me!

645
00:43:24,387 --> 00:43:26,597
Sir, there's no sign of Rider.

646
00:43:26,681 --> 00:43:28,307
(NEIGHING)

647
00:43:30,602 --> 00:43:31,602
Maximus!

648
00:43:31,895 --> 00:43:34,647
(SNIFFING)

649
00:43:37,067 --> 00:43:38,067
(GRUNTING)

650
00:43:39,653 --> 00:43:41,487
What's he doing?

651
00:43:41,947 --> 00:43:43,030
(NEIGHS)

652
00:43:44,991 --> 00:43:46,075
(SNUFFLES)

653
00:43:50,372 --> 00:43:52,957
A passage! Come on, men. Let's go.

654
00:43:53,917 --> 00:43:56,752
Conli! Make sure those boys
don't get away.

655
00:43:59,673 --> 00:44:00,714
(GRUNTS)

656
00:44:01,049 --> 00:44:02,508
Play it safe

657
00:44:04,219 --> 00:44:06,011
or go get the crown?

658
00:44:08,098 --> 00:44:09,640
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

659
00:44:14,020 --> 00:44:17,940
(SLURRING) I got a dream
<i>I got some dreams</i>

660
00:44:19,150 --> 00:44:22,528
Oh! Somebody get me a glass!

661
00:44:22,612 --> 00:44:26,365
Because I just found me
a tall drink of water.

662
00:44:27,033 --> 00:44:29,034
Oh, stop it, you big lug.

663
00:44:29,119 --> 00:44:30,160
(LAUGHS)

664
00:44:31,037 --> 00:44:32,955
Where does that tunnel let out?

665
00:44:33,039 --> 00:44:34,456
Knife!

666
00:44:36,877 --> 00:44:41,797
I didn't know you had that in you
back there. That was pretty impressive.

667
00:44:41,882 --> 00:44:43,173
I know!

668
00:44:44,885 --> 00:44:46,343
I know.

669
00:44:49,347 --> 00:44:52,683
So... Flynn? Where are you from?

670
00:44:52,767 --> 00:44:55,227
Whoa! Sorry, blondie,
I don't do back-story.

671
00:44:55,312 --> 00:44:57,897
However, I am becoming
very interested in yours.

672
00:44:57,981 --> 00:45:00,566
I know I'm not supposed
to mention the hair.

673
00:45:00,650 --> 00:45:02,192
- Nope.
- Or the mother.

674
00:45:02,277 --> 00:45:04,904
- Uh-uh.
- I'm too scared to ask about the frog.

675
00:45:05,071 --> 00:45:06,447
- Chameleon.
- Nuance.

676
00:45:06,740 --> 00:45:11,243
Here's my question, though,
if you want to see the lanterns so badly

677
00:45:11,328 --> 00:45:13,245
why haven't you gone before?

678
00:45:13,538 --> 00:45:15,331
Uh... (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

679
00:45:15,874 --> 00:45:17,082
Well...

680
00:45:18,418 --> 00:45:19,501
(RUMBLING)

681
00:45:20,837 --> 00:45:22,046
Uh, Flynn?

682
00:45:24,257 --> 00:45:25,382
Flynn?

683
00:45:25,926 --> 00:45:27,134
- Rider?
- (MAXIMUS NEIGHING)

684
00:45:27,218 --> 00:45:29,178
Run. Run!

685
00:45:47,489 --> 00:45:49,823
- Who's that?
- They don't like me.

686
00:45:50,367 --> 00:45:52,326
- Who's that?
- They don't like me either.

687
00:45:52,410 --> 00:45:54,328
- (NEIGHING FIERCELY)
- Who's that?

688
00:45:54,412 --> 00:45:57,373
Let's assume that everyone in here
doesn't like me.

689
00:45:57,457 --> 00:45:58,624
- Here.
- (GRUNTS)

690
00:46:05,966 --> 00:46:07,424
- (CHUCKLING)
- (GASPS)

691
00:46:07,634 --> 00:46:09,718
I waited a long time for this.

692
00:46:09,970 --> 00:46:10,970
(WHIMPERS)

693
00:46:11,054 --> 00:46:12,221
(GRUNTING)

694
00:46:19,145 --> 00:46:22,815
Oh, mama!
I have got to get me one of these!

695
00:46:22,941 --> 00:46:23,983
Ha!

696
00:46:24,359 --> 00:46:25,526
(NEIGHS)

697
00:46:25,694 --> 00:46:27,069
(NEIGHING CHALLENGINGLY)

698
00:46:27,153 --> 00:46:29,738
(FLYNN GRUNTING)

699
00:46:31,157 --> 00:46:35,494
You should know that this
is the strangest thing I've ever done!

700
00:46:38,456 --> 00:46:40,666
(DISTANT CLATTERING)

701
00:46:40,750 --> 00:46:42,626
How about two out of three?

702
00:46:42,711 --> 00:46:43,711
Flynn!

703
00:46:45,422 --> 00:46:46,463
(GRUNTS)

704
00:46:47,007 --> 00:46:48,090
(NEIGHS IN SURPRISE)

705
00:46:49,300 --> 00:46:50,843
Flynn, look out!

706
00:46:51,177 --> 00:46:52,219
(EXCLAIMING)

707
00:46:55,056 --> 00:46:58,183
Ha! You should see your faces,
because you look...

708
00:46:59,102 --> 00:47:00,686
(GASPING)... ridiculous.

709
00:47:00,770 --> 00:47:01,895
(THUDDING)

710
00:47:07,819 --> 00:47:10,529
Come on, blondie! Jump!

711
00:47:11,364 --> 00:47:13,490
(NEIGHING FIERCELY)

712
00:47:48,359 --> 00:47:49,401
(MAN SCREAMS)

713
00:48:00,413 --> 00:48:01,538
(RAPUNZEL SCREAMS)

714
00:48:15,929 --> 00:48:16,929
(FLYNN INHALES)

715
00:48:19,724 --> 00:48:20,849
(PANTING)

716
00:48:20,934 --> 00:48:21,934
(INHALES)

717
00:48:24,896 --> 00:48:26,105
(GASPS)

718
00:48:26,981 --> 00:48:29,983
(GRUNTING)

719
00:48:30,110 --> 00:48:31,151
(EXCLAIMS IN PAIN)

720
00:48:32,529 --> 00:48:33,529
(INHALES)

721
00:48:35,490 --> 00:48:37,574
(GRUNTING)

722
00:48:38,326 --> 00:48:39,409
(GASPING)

723
00:48:39,494 --> 00:48:42,538
It's no use. I can't see anything.

724
00:48:42,872 --> 00:48:44,540
(BREATHING SHALLOWLY)

725
00:48:44,624 --> 00:48:45,624
(INHALES)

726
00:48:47,961 --> 00:48:51,130
Hey, there's no point.
It's pitch-black down there.

727
00:48:59,180 --> 00:49:01,014
(DEJECTEDLY) This is all my fault.

728
00:49:02,725 --> 00:49:05,811
She was right.
I never should have done this.

729
00:49:06,146 --> 00:49:07,521
(SNIFFLES)

730
00:49:09,649 --> 00:49:10,816
I'm so...

731
00:49:11,985 --> 00:49:14,069
I'm so sorry, Flynn.

732
00:49:16,364 --> 00:49:17,656
(CRYING)

733
00:49:19,033 --> 00:49:20,284
(SIGHS)

734
00:49:21,828 --> 00:49:23,036
Eugene.

735
00:49:24,497 --> 00:49:25,622
What?

736
00:49:26,666 --> 00:49:29,168
My real name is Eugene Fitzherbert.

737
00:49:30,753 --> 00:49:32,838
Someone might as well know.

738
00:49:33,256 --> 00:49:34,339
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

739
00:49:35,675 --> 00:49:38,468
I have magic hair
that glows when I sing.

740
00:49:39,179 --> 00:49:40,345
What?

741
00:49:42,223 --> 00:49:46,268
I have magic hair that glows
when I sing!

742
00:49:47,729 --> 00:49:50,564
(SINGING) Flower gleam and glow
<i>Let your power shine</i>

743
00:49:50,732 --> 00:49:51,982
(BOTH INHALING)

744
00:49:58,239 --> 00:49:59,364
(EXCLAIMS)

745
00:50:33,858 --> 00:50:34,983
(GASPS)

746
00:50:35,068 --> 00:50:36,610
(BOTH COUGHING)

747
00:50:41,241 --> 00:50:42,824
We made it.

748
00:50:42,909 --> 00:50:46,370
- Her hair glows.
- We're alive. I'm alive!

749
00:50:46,454 --> 00:50:48,080
- I didn't see that coming.
- Eugene?

750
00:50:48,164 --> 00:50:50,040
The hair actually glows.

751
00:50:50,124 --> 00:50:51,750
- Why does her hair glow?
- Eugene!

752
00:50:51,834 --> 00:50:52,834
What?

753
00:50:54,545 --> 00:50:56,838
It doesn't just glow.

754
00:50:59,259 --> 00:51:01,301
Why is he smiling at me?

755
00:51:09,644 --> 00:51:12,938
(MEN COUGHING)

756
00:51:16,943 --> 00:51:18,277
(WHEEZING)

757
00:51:18,361 --> 00:51:22,823
(COUGHING)

758
00:51:25,451 --> 00:51:28,287
I'll kill him. I'll kill that Rider!

759
00:51:29,789 --> 00:51:33,792
We'll cut him off at the kingdom
and get back the crown. Come on!

760
00:51:35,044 --> 00:51:36,461
GOTHEL: Or...

761
00:51:38,256 --> 00:51:41,174
Perhaps you want to stop
acting like wild dogs

762
00:51:41,259 --> 00:51:44,636
chasing their tails
and think for a moment.

763
00:51:46,848 --> 00:51:49,266
(SCOFFS) Oh, please,
there's no need for that.

764
00:51:50,977 --> 00:51:52,728
(BOTH GRUNTING)

765
00:51:53,563 --> 00:51:54,646
(CHUCKLING)

766
00:51:54,897 --> 00:51:58,400
Well, if that's all you desire,
then be on your way.

767
00:51:58,484 --> 00:52:01,486
I was going to offer you something
worth 1,000 crowns.

768
00:52:01,571 --> 00:52:03,196
Would have made you
rich beyond belief,

769
00:52:03,281 --> 00:52:05,073
and that wasn't even the best part.
(LAUGHING)

770
00:52:05,158 --> 00:52:09,161
Oh, well. C'est la vie. Enjoy your crown!

771
00:52:10,663 --> 00:52:12,331
What's the best part?

772
00:52:12,832 --> 00:52:17,794
It comes with revenge on Flynn Rider.

773
00:52:24,802 --> 00:52:26,636
You're being strangely cryptic

774
00:52:26,721 --> 00:52:29,181
as you wrap your magic hair
around my injured hand.

775
00:52:29,265 --> 00:52:30,307
(GROANS)

776
00:52:30,683 --> 00:52:31,975
Sorry.

777
00:52:32,060 --> 00:52:33,101
(EXHALES)

778
00:52:33,186 --> 00:52:37,230
Just don't... Don't freak out.

779
00:52:39,650 --> 00:52:40,859
(SIGHS)

780
00:52:42,862 --> 00:52:46,531
(SINGING) Flower, gleam and glow

781
00:52:47,200 --> 00:52:50,160
<i>Let your power shine</i>

782
00:52:51,537 --> 00:52:54,915
<i>Make the clock reverse</i>

783
00:52:54,999 --> 00:52:58,752
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

784
00:53:00,171 --> 00:53:03,006
<i>Heal what has been hurt</i>

785
00:53:04,050 --> 00:53:07,302
<i>Change the Fates' design</i>

786
00:53:08,388 --> 00:53:11,640
<i>Save what has been lost</i>

787
00:53:11,724 --> 00:53:14,893
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

788
00:53:15,561 --> 00:53:20,315
<i>What once was mine</i>

789
00:53:27,907 --> 00:53:29,157
(WHIMPERS)

790
00:53:30,034 --> 00:53:31,785
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

791
00:53:32,412 --> 00:53:34,579
(SCREAM BUILDING)

792
00:53:34,664 --> 00:53:36,665
Please don't freak out!

793
00:53:36,749 --> 00:53:38,291
(STRANGLED GASPING)

794
00:53:39,752 --> 00:53:41,878
I'm not freaking out.
Are you freaking out?

795
00:53:41,963 --> 00:53:45,215
I'm just interested in your hair
and the magical qualities it possesses.

796
00:53:45,299 --> 00:53:48,093
How long has it been
doing that exactly?

797
00:53:49,345 --> 00:53:51,680
Forever, I guess.

798
00:53:52,557 --> 00:53:55,851
Mother says when I was a baby,
people tried to cut it.

799
00:53:55,935 --> 00:53:57,853
They wanted to take it for themselves.

800
00:53:58,438 --> 00:54:03,358
But once it's cut,
it turns brown and loses its power.

801
00:54:04,193 --> 00:54:07,320
A gift like that, it has to be protected.

802
00:54:08,281 --> 00:54:10,699
That's why Mother never let me...

803
00:54:11,868 --> 00:54:13,118
(SIGHS)

804
00:54:14,120 --> 00:54:17,122
That's why I never left and...

805
00:54:19,083 --> 00:54:20,083
(SIGHS)

806
00:54:20,543 --> 00:54:22,586
You never left that tower.

807
00:54:26,299 --> 00:54:28,467
And you're still going to go back?

808
00:54:28,759 --> 00:54:31,011
No! Yes.

809
00:54:31,721 --> 00:54:33,096
(GRUNTS IN FRUSTRATION)

810
00:54:33,181 --> 00:54:35,140
It's complicated.

811
00:54:43,399 --> 00:54:44,649
(EXHALES)

812
00:54:45,651 --> 00:54:48,653
So, Eugene Fitzherbert, huh?

813
00:54:48,863 --> 00:54:50,780
Ah, yeah. Well...

814
00:54:50,865 --> 00:54:54,201
I'll spare you the sob story
of poor orphan Eugene Fitzherbert.

815
00:54:54,285 --> 00:54:57,579
It's a little bit of a downer.

816
00:55:00,666 --> 00:55:02,042
(CHUCKLES)

817
00:55:03,836 --> 00:55:07,839
There was this book I used to read
every night to all the younger kids.

818
00:55:07,924 --> 00:55:09,591
<i>The Tales of Flynnagan Rider.</i>

819
00:55:09,675 --> 00:55:14,262
Swashbuckling rogue, richest man
alive, not bad with the ladies either.

820
00:55:14,347 --> 00:55:16,598
Not that he'd ever brag about it,
of course.

821
00:55:16,682 --> 00:55:19,226
(CHUCKLES) Was he a thief, too?

822
00:55:19,310 --> 00:55:20,352
Uh...

823
00:55:21,062 --> 00:55:22,521
Well, no.

824
00:55:23,147 --> 00:55:26,024
He had enough money to do anything
that he wanted to do.

825
00:55:26,108 --> 00:55:27,692
He could go anywhere
that he wanted to go.

826
00:55:28,444 --> 00:55:32,447
And for a kid with nothing,
I don't know, I...

827
00:55:34,116 --> 00:55:35,659
Just seemed like the better option.

828
00:55:35,743 --> 00:55:36,868
(RAPUNZEL CHUCKLES)

829
00:55:37,036 --> 00:55:39,496
You can't tell anyone about this, okay?

830
00:55:39,914 --> 00:55:42,040
It could ruin my whole reputation.

831
00:55:42,166 --> 00:55:44,709
Ah. We wouldn't want that.

832
00:55:44,794 --> 00:55:47,087
A fake reputation is all a man has.

833
00:55:47,171 --> 00:55:49,506
(CHUCKLES)

834
00:55:54,136 --> 00:55:55,136
(CLEARS THROAT NERVOUSLY)

835
00:55:55,429 --> 00:55:57,180
Well, I should...

836
00:55:58,391 --> 00:56:00,725
(STAMMERING) I should get
some more firewood.

837
00:56:01,686 --> 00:56:02,936
RAPUNZEL: Hey.

838
00:56:03,396 --> 00:56:09,067
For the record, I like Eugene Fitzherbert
much better than Flynn Rider.

839
00:56:10,903 --> 00:56:11,987
Well.

840
00:56:12,238 --> 00:56:15,407
Then you'd be the first. But thank you.

841
00:56:25,209 --> 00:56:28,503
Well, I thought he'd never leave.

842
00:56:28,588 --> 00:56:29,963
Mother?

843
00:56:30,047 --> 00:56:31,548
Hello, dear.

844
00:56:31,757 --> 00:56:33,550
(RAPUNZEL STAMMERING
NERVOUSLY)

845
00:56:34,677 --> 00:56:35,969
How did you find me?

846
00:56:36,262 --> 00:56:38,138
Oh, it was easy, really.

847
00:56:38,222 --> 00:56:42,601
I just listened for the sound of complete
and utter betrayal and followed that.

848
00:56:43,019 --> 00:56:45,103
(SIGHS) Mother...

849
00:56:45,313 --> 00:56:49,190
- We're going home. Now.
- You don't understand.

850
00:56:49,275 --> 00:56:53,695
I've been on this incredible journey,
and I've seen and learned so much.

851
00:56:54,614 --> 00:56:55,780
I even met someone.

852
00:56:55,865 --> 00:56:58,950
Yes, the wanted thief. I'm so proud.
Come on.

853
00:56:59,285 --> 00:57:01,953
Mother, wait. I think...

854
00:57:03,664 --> 00:57:05,165
I think he likes me.

855
00:57:05,416 --> 00:57:08,126
Likes you?
Please, Rapunzel, that's demented!

856
00:57:08,294 --> 00:57:09,336
(PROTESTING)

857
00:57:09,420 --> 00:57:11,338
(SINGING) This is why
<i>you never should have left</i>

858
00:57:12,214 --> 00:57:15,383
<i>Dear, this whole romance</i>
<i>that you've invented</i>

859
00:57:15,468 --> 00:57:20,013
<i>Just proves you're too naive to be here</i>

860
00:57:20,556 --> 00:57:23,433
<i>Why would he like you?</i>
<i>Come on now, really</i>

861
00:57:24,060 --> 00:57:27,145
<i>Look at you!</i>
<i>You think that he's impressed?</i>

862
00:57:27,688 --> 00:57:31,441
<i>Don't be a dummy, come with Mummy</i>

863
00:57:32,109 --> 00:57:33,568
<i>Mother...</i>

864
00:57:33,653 --> 00:57:34,986
No!

865
00:57:35,821 --> 00:57:37,197
No?

866
00:57:38,157 --> 00:57:41,826
<i>Oh, I see how it is</i>

867
00:57:44,163 --> 00:57:47,916
<i>Rapunzel knows best</i>
<i>Rapunzel's so mature now</i>

868
00:57:48,000 --> 00:57:51,002
<i>Such a clever grown-up miss</i>

869
00:57:51,504 --> 00:57:55,090
<i>Rapunzel knows best</i>
<i>Fine, if you're so sure now</i>

870
00:57:55,174 --> 00:57:58,551
<i>- Go ahead, then give him this!</i>
<i>- How did you...</i>

871
00:57:58,761 --> 00:58:02,138
<i>This is why he's here</i>
<i>Don't let him deceive you</i>

872
00:58:02,223 --> 00:58:04,432
<i>Give it to him, watch, you'll see</i>

873
00:58:04,517 --> 00:58:05,475
I will!

874
00:58:05,559 --> 00:58:08,812
<i>Trust me, my dear</i>
<i>That's how fast he'll leave you</i>

875
00:58:09,146 --> 00:58:12,565
<i>I won't say I told you so</i>

876
00:58:12,650 --> 00:58:17,028
<i>No, Rapunzel knows best</i>
<i>So, if he's such a dreamboat</i>

877
00:58:17,113 --> 00:58:19,531
<i>Go and put him to the test</i>

878
00:58:19,615 --> 00:58:20,615
Mother, wait!

879
00:58:20,700 --> 00:58:26,287
<i>If he's lying, don't come crying</i>

880
00:58:27,206 --> 00:58:32,085
<i>Mother knows best</i>

881
00:58:37,800 --> 00:58:41,386
FLYNN: So, can I ask you something?

882
00:58:42,388 --> 00:58:45,724
Is there any chance that I'm going to get
super strength in my hand?

883
00:58:45,808 --> 00:58:49,269
Because I'm not going to lie.
That would be stupendous.

884
00:58:50,312 --> 00:58:51,771
Hey, you all right?

885
00:58:52,231 --> 00:58:58,027
Oh! Sorry, yes.
Just lost in thought, I guess.

886
00:59:00,656 --> 00:59:01,823
Here's the thing,

887
00:59:01,907 --> 00:59:05,201
superhuman good looks,
I've always had them. Born with it.

888
00:59:05,286 --> 00:59:09,497
But superhuman strength. Can you
imagine the possibilities of this?

889
00:59:13,753 --> 00:59:15,754
Patience, boys.

890
00:59:16,380 --> 00:59:20,550
All good things to those who wait.

891
00:59:23,846 --> 00:59:26,598
(SNORING SOFTLY)

892
00:59:32,980 --> 00:59:34,314
(MUMBLES SLEEPILY)

893
00:59:35,232 --> 00:59:36,483
Huh?

894
00:59:36,650 --> 00:59:39,027
(SNORTING)

895
00:59:39,945 --> 00:59:42,447
Well, I hope you're here to apologize.

896
00:59:42,823 --> 00:59:45,241
(FLYNN SCREAMING)

897
00:59:45,451 --> 00:59:48,036
No, put me down. Stop it! No!

898
00:59:48,120 --> 00:59:50,747
- Let me go!
- (NEIGHING FIERCELY)

899
00:59:50,831 --> 00:59:52,624
(GRUNTING) Give me him!

900
00:59:52,917 --> 00:59:54,709
- (NEIGHING)
- FLYNN: Stop, stop, stop!

901
00:59:55,586 --> 00:59:56,795
(FLYNN EXCLAIMS)

902
00:59:57,213 --> 00:59:58,213
(NICKERING GROGGILY)

903
00:59:58,964 --> 01:00:01,007
(NEIGHING)

904
01:00:01,091 --> 01:00:04,719
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

905
01:00:04,804 --> 01:00:06,805
Easy, boy. Easy! Settle down.

906
01:00:07,056 --> 01:00:08,932
(NEIGHING FIERCELY)

907
01:00:09,016 --> 01:00:10,391
Easy, boy. Easy.

908
01:00:10,684 --> 01:00:12,435
(SOOTHINGLY) Easy.

909
01:00:14,146 --> 01:00:15,772
That's it.

910
01:00:19,109 --> 01:00:20,193
Now sit.

911
01:00:20,444 --> 01:00:21,694
(NEIGHS)

912
01:00:21,987 --> 01:00:23,112
(FIRMLY) Sit!

913
01:00:23,656 --> 01:00:25,657
- FLYNN: What?
- Now drop the boot.

914
01:00:26,200 --> 01:00:27,492
Drop it.

915
01:00:28,994 --> 01:00:29,994
(COOING) Aw!

916
01:00:30,079 --> 01:00:34,457
You're such a good boy! Yes, you are!

917
01:00:34,542 --> 01:00:35,708
(CHUCKLING AFFECTIONATELY)

918
01:00:36,085 --> 01:00:39,671
You all tired from chasing this bad man
all over the place?

919
01:00:39,755 --> 01:00:43,633
- FLYNN: Excuse me?
- Nobody appreciates you, do they?

920
01:00:43,717 --> 01:00:44,884
- Do they?
- (SNORTS)

921
01:00:44,969 --> 01:00:47,011
Oh, come on. He's a bad horse!

922
01:00:47,096 --> 01:00:49,722
Oh, he's nothing but a big sweetheart.

923
01:00:49,807 --> 01:00:50,807
(NEIGHS HAPPILY)

924
01:00:50,891 --> 01:00:52,308
Isn't that right...

925
01:00:52,852 --> 01:00:54,352
Maximus?

926
01:00:55,020 --> 01:00:57,438
You've got to be kidding me.

927
01:00:57,523 --> 01:01:02,235
Look. Today is kind of
the biggest day of my life,

928
01:01:02,820 --> 01:01:06,656
and the thing is,
I need you not to get him arrested.

929
01:01:06,740 --> 01:01:08,658
- (HUFFS)
- Just for 24 hours,

930
01:01:08,742 --> 01:01:11,953
and then you can chase each other
to your heart's content.

931
01:01:12,037 --> 01:01:13,162
Okay?

932
01:01:13,247 --> 01:01:14,497
(SIGHS)

933
01:01:16,208 --> 01:01:17,208
(GRUNTS)

934
01:01:17,293 --> 01:01:20,795
And it's also my birthday.
Just so you know.

935
01:01:20,880 --> 01:01:22,005
(SNORTS)

936
01:01:33,475 --> 01:01:34,726
(GRUNTS)

937
01:01:49,241 --> 01:01:50,241
- (NEIGHS)
- (CHUCKLES CONTENTEDLY)

938
01:01:51,160 --> 01:01:52,201
(LAUGHING)

939
01:01:54,246 --> 01:01:55,830
- (NEIGHING IN RAGE)
- (PASCAL SQUEAKS)

940
01:01:55,915 --> 01:01:57,498
(GROWLING)

941
01:02:02,588 --> 01:02:04,714
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

942
01:02:10,012 --> 01:02:11,387
- (BLEATING)
- (GASPS)

943
01:02:11,972 --> 01:02:14,265
- (PEOPLE EXCLAIMING)
- Excuse me. Sorry.

944
01:02:22,775 --> 01:02:24,067
(FLYNN WHISTLES)

945
01:02:25,569 --> 01:02:26,611
(ALL GASP)

946
01:02:27,071 --> 01:02:30,782
(ALL LAUGHING)

947
01:02:35,287 --> 01:02:37,038
(GASPING IN AWE)

948
01:02:37,122 --> 01:02:39,040
Thank you!

949
01:02:40,751 --> 01:02:42,168
(NICKERING)

950
01:02:54,723 --> 01:02:56,557
It's for the lost princess.

951
01:03:10,739 --> 01:03:12,407
(MUSICIANS PLAYING LIVELY MUSIC)

952
01:03:17,663 --> 01:03:18,663
(EXCLAIMS)

953
01:03:19,790 --> 01:03:21,582
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

954
01:03:34,388 --> 01:03:35,388
(LAUGHING)

955
01:04:13,302 --> 01:04:15,178
(CROWD CHEERING)

956
01:04:15,262 --> 01:04:16,763
MAN: To the boats!

957
01:04:25,731 --> 01:04:26,731
(NICKERS SOFTLY)

958
01:04:28,025 --> 01:04:29,067
Hey, Max!

959
01:04:32,446 --> 01:04:35,323
What? I bought them.

960
01:04:38,202 --> 01:04:39,994
- Most of them.
- (NICKERS QUESTIONINGLY)

961
01:04:41,371 --> 01:04:42,955
Where are we going?

962
01:04:43,040 --> 01:04:46,918
Best day of your life?
I figured you should have a decent seat.

963
01:05:02,684 --> 01:05:04,102
(SIGHS)

964
01:05:05,437 --> 01:05:06,813
You okay?

965
01:05:07,648 --> 01:05:09,273
(SOFTLY) I'm terrified.

966
01:05:10,150 --> 01:05:11,442
Why?

967
01:05:12,236 --> 01:05:16,531
I've been looking out a window
for 18 years,

968
01:05:16,615 --> 01:05:21,452
dreaming about what it might feel like
when those lights rise in the sky.

969
01:05:22,913 --> 01:05:26,415
What if it's not everything
that I dreamed it would be?

970
01:05:28,961 --> 01:05:30,336
It will be.

971
01:05:31,797 --> 01:05:36,425
And what if it is? What do I do then?

972
01:05:36,885 --> 01:05:41,806
That's the good part, I guess.
You get to go find a new dream.

973
01:05:42,099 --> 01:05:43,182
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

974
01:07:15,484 --> 01:07:20,529
RAPUNZEL: (SINGING) All those days
<i>watching from the windows</i>

975
01:07:20,614 --> 01:07:24,242
<i>All those years, outside looking in</i>

976
01:07:25,077 --> 01:07:29,872
<i>All that time, never even knowing</i>

977
01:07:29,957 --> 01:07:34,752
<i>Just how blind I've been</i>

978
01:07:35,379 --> 01:07:39,924
<i>Now I'm here, blinking in the starlight</i>

979
01:07:40,425 --> 01:07:44,345
<i>Now I'm here, suddenly I see</i>

980
01:07:44,721 --> 01:07:49,392
<i>Standing here, it's, oh, so clear</i>

981
01:07:49,476 --> 01:07:54,063
<i>I'm where I'm meant to be</i>

982
01:07:54,147 --> 01:07:58,442
<i>And at last I see the light</i>

983
01:07:58,777 --> 01:08:02,780
<i>And it's like the fog has lifted</i>

984
01:08:03,448 --> 01:08:08,035
<i>And at last I see the light</i>

985
01:08:08,120 --> 01:08:11,914
<i>And it's like the sky is new</i>

986
01:08:12,749 --> 01:08:17,378
<i>And it's warm and real and bright</i>

987
01:08:17,462 --> 01:08:22,800
<i>And the world has somehow shifted</i>

988
01:08:25,804 --> 01:08:30,725
<i>All at once, everything looks different</i>

989
01:08:30,809 --> 01:08:35,104
<i>Now that I see you</i>

990
01:08:40,485 --> 01:08:41,610
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

991
01:08:41,903 --> 01:08:44,405
I have something for you, too.

992
01:08:44,781 --> 01:08:47,992
I should have given it to you before,
but I was just scared.

993
01:08:48,327 --> 01:08:52,913
And the thing is, I'm not scared
anymore. You know what I mean?

994
01:08:54,791 --> 01:08:57,001
I'm starting to.

995
01:09:01,048 --> 01:09:05,593
FLYNN: All those days
<i>chasing down a daydream</i>

996
01:09:06,011 --> 01:09:09,805
<i>All those years, living in a blur</i>

997
01:09:10,349 --> 01:09:14,935
<i>All that time, never truly seeing</i>

998
01:09:15,020 --> 01:09:18,689
<i>Things the way they were</i>

999
01:09:19,775 --> 01:09:24,612
<i>Now she's here, shining in the starlight</i>

1000
01:09:24,696 --> 01:09:28,699
<i>Now she's here, suddenly I know</i>

1001
01:09:29,201 --> 01:09:33,788
<i>If she's here, it's crystal clear</i>

1002
01:09:33,872 --> 01:09:37,958
<i>I'm where I'm meant to go</i>

1003
01:09:38,043 --> 01:09:42,630
<i>BOTH: And at last I see the light</i>

1004
01:09:42,714 --> 01:09:46,842
<i>And it's like the fog has lifted</i>

1005
01:09:46,927 --> 01:09:51,263
<i>And at last I see the light</i>

1006
01:09:51,348 --> 01:09:55,476
<i>And it's like the sky is new</i>

1007
01:09:55,727 --> 01:10:00,356
<i>And it's warm and real and bright</i>

1008
01:10:00,440 --> 01:10:05,903
<i>And the world has somehow shifted</i>

1009
01:10:08,949 --> 01:10:13,994
<i>All at once, everything is different</i>

1010
01:10:14,079 --> 01:10:19,583
<i>Now that I see you</i>

1011
01:10:23,046 --> 01:10:25,214
<i>Now that I...</i>

1012
01:10:26,258 --> 01:10:29,635
<i>see you</i>

1013
01:10:49,239 --> 01:10:51,907
Is everything okay?

1014
01:10:51,992 --> 01:10:53,033
Huh?

1015
01:10:53,910 --> 01:10:55,703
Oh, yes. (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

1016
01:10:56,037 --> 01:10:58,873
Yes, of course. I just...

1017
01:11:04,629 --> 01:11:06,964
I'm sorry. Everything is fine.

1018
01:11:07,507 --> 01:11:09,592
There's just something
I have to take care of.

1019
01:11:12,471 --> 01:11:13,554
Okay.

1020
01:11:15,307 --> 01:11:17,099
I'll be right back.

1021
01:11:21,313 --> 01:11:22,605
(SQUEAKS)

1022
01:11:23,273 --> 01:11:25,149
It's all right, Pascal.

1023
01:11:32,532 --> 01:11:34,408
FLYNN: Ah! There you are!

1024
01:11:34,493 --> 01:11:37,077
I've been searching everywhere
for you guys since we got separated.

1025
01:11:37,162 --> 01:11:41,415
The sideburns are coming in nice, huh?
Got to be excited about that.

1026
01:11:43,668 --> 01:11:45,044
(CLEARS THROAT)

1027
01:11:45,128 --> 01:11:47,880
Anyhow, I just wanted to say
I shouldn't have split.

1028
01:11:47,964 --> 01:11:51,759
The crown is all yours. I'll miss you,
but I think it's for the

1029
01:11:52,385 --> 01:11:53,427
best.

1030
01:11:55,096 --> 01:11:58,516
Holding out on us again, eh, Rider?

1031
01:11:58,975 --> 01:12:01,894
- What?
- We heard you found something.

1032
01:12:01,978 --> 01:12:04,855
Something much more valuable
than a crown.

1033
01:12:05,857 --> 01:12:08,692
We want her instead.

1034
01:12:17,827 --> 01:12:18,869
(EXHALES)

1035
01:12:18,954 --> 01:12:22,206
I was starting to think you ran off
with the crown and left me.

1036
01:12:29,256 --> 01:12:30,881
He did.

1037
01:12:31,007 --> 01:12:34,218
What? No. He wouldn't.

1038
01:12:35,178 --> 01:12:36,845
See for yourself.

1039
01:12:41,726 --> 01:12:42,810
Eugene?

1040
01:12:45,522 --> 01:12:47,439
Eugene!

1041
01:12:49,693 --> 01:12:54,655
A fair trade. A crown
for the girl with the magic hair.

1042
01:12:55,865 --> 01:12:59,660
How much do you think someone would
pay to stay young and healthy forever?

1043
01:12:59,744 --> 01:13:02,663
No. Please. No!

1044
01:13:03,415 --> 01:13:04,456
No!

1045
01:13:07,586 --> 01:13:08,752
(SCREAMS)

1046
01:13:09,713 --> 01:13:11,213
- (THUDDING)
- (MEN GRUNTING)

1047
01:13:12,257 --> 01:13:13,549
GOTHEL: Rapunzel!

1048
01:13:15,260 --> 01:13:16,677
Mother?

1049
01:13:18,847 --> 01:13:21,223
(PANTING)

1050
01:13:21,558 --> 01:13:24,059
Oh, my precious girl!

1051
01:13:24,936 --> 01:13:26,186
Mother.

1052
01:13:26,730 --> 01:13:29,106
Are you all right? Are you hurt?

1053
01:13:29,190 --> 01:13:32,735
- How did you...
- I was so worried about you, dear.

1054
01:13:32,819 --> 01:13:36,363
So I followed you.
And I saw them attack you and...

1055
01:13:36,448 --> 01:13:39,116
Oh, my. Let's go before they come to!

1056
01:14:06,394 --> 01:14:08,270
(CRYING)

1057
01:14:09,314 --> 01:14:13,275
You were right, Mother.
You were right about everything.

1058
01:14:14,444 --> 01:14:17,821
I know, darling. I know.

1059
01:14:23,495 --> 01:14:25,746
(BOAT HULL CREAKING)

1060
01:14:27,749 --> 01:14:29,792
(SCRAPING)

1061
01:14:31,670 --> 01:14:32,753
Look!

1062
01:14:33,338 --> 01:14:34,713
The crown!

1063
01:14:35,548 --> 01:14:36,840
(GROGGILY) Rapunzel.

1064
01:14:37,509 --> 01:14:38,926
- Rapunzel!
- (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1065
01:14:41,012 --> 01:14:43,764
- FLYNN: No! Wait, guys!
- (NICKERS QUESTIONINGLY)

1066
01:14:46,601 --> 01:14:48,352
FLYNN: Rapunzel!

1067
01:15:04,786 --> 01:15:05,994
(DOOR OPENS)

1068
01:15:07,580 --> 01:15:09,707
Let's get this over with, Rider.

1069
01:15:11,793 --> 01:15:13,127
Where are we going?

1070
01:15:16,798 --> 01:15:17,840
Oh.

1071
01:15:20,969 --> 01:15:23,721
There. It never happened.

1072
01:15:25,974 --> 01:15:30,894
Now, wash up for dinner.
I'm making hazelnut soup.

1073
01:15:34,691 --> 01:15:40,696
(SIGHS) I really did try, Rapunzel.
I tried to warn you what was out there.

1074
01:15:41,364 --> 01:15:45,826
The world is dark and selfish and cruel.

1075
01:15:45,910 --> 01:15:48,912
If it finds
even the slightest ray of sunshine,

1076
01:15:49,831 --> 01:15:51,582
it destroys it.

1077
01:16:04,804 --> 01:16:09,266
(SQUEAKING SADLY)

1078
01:16:14,939 --> 01:16:16,940
(SIGHS)

1079
01:17:16,125 --> 01:17:17,376
(GROANS)

1080
01:17:30,682 --> 01:17:32,015
(GRUNTING)

1081
01:17:34,310 --> 01:17:36,478
How did you know about her?
Tell me, now!

1082
01:17:36,563 --> 01:17:39,398
It wasn't us! It was the old lady!

1083
01:17:39,482 --> 01:17:40,732
Old lady?

1084
01:17:41,067 --> 01:17:42,109
(GRUNTS)

1085
01:17:42,193 --> 01:17:44,361
Wait. No! Wait!

1086
01:17:44,445 --> 01:17:47,364
You don't understand!
She's in trouble! Wait!

1087
01:17:47,699 --> 01:17:48,866
Rapunzel?

1088
01:17:50,577 --> 01:17:52,369
What's going on up there?

1089
01:17:52,579 --> 01:17:56,039
(PANTING)

1090
01:17:56,541 --> 01:17:58,208
Are you all right?

1091
01:17:59,544 --> 01:18:01,086
I'm the lost princess.

1092
01:18:01,212 --> 01:18:04,965
(SIGHS) Please speak up, Rapunzel.
You know how I hate the mumbling.

1093
01:18:05,049 --> 01:18:07,885
(LOUDLY) I am the lost princess.

1094
01:18:07,969 --> 01:18:09,636
Aren't I?

1095
01:18:11,806 --> 01:18:14,057
Did I mumble, Mother?

1096
01:18:15,226 --> 01:18:17,728
Or should I even call you that?

1097
01:18:18,980 --> 01:18:21,815
Oh, Rapunzel,
do you even hear yourself?

1098
01:18:21,900 --> 01:18:24,610
Why would you ask
such a ridiculous question?

1099
01:18:24,694 --> 01:18:28,155
It was you! It was all you!

1100
01:18:30,241 --> 01:18:33,744
Everything I did was to protect you.

1101
01:18:35,079 --> 01:18:36,330
- (GRUNTS)
- Rapunzel!

1102
01:18:36,414 --> 01:18:39,416
I've spent my entire life
hiding from people

1103
01:18:39,500 --> 01:18:41,835
- who would use me for my power...
- Rapunzel!

1104
01:18:41,920 --> 01:18:44,922
...when I should have been hiding
from you!

1105
01:18:45,006 --> 01:18:48,300
Where will you go?
He won't be there for you.

1106
01:18:48,384 --> 01:18:50,260
RAPUNZEL: What did you do to him?

1107
01:18:50,762 --> 01:18:54,014
GOTHEL: That criminal is to be hanged
<i>for his crimes.</i>

1108
01:18:54,098 --> 01:18:57,517
- (GASPS) No.
- Now, now, it's all right.

1109
01:18:57,602 --> 01:19:02,189
Listen to me.
All of this is as it should be.

1110
01:19:02,607 --> 01:19:06,109
No! You were wrong about the world.

1111
01:19:06,653 --> 01:19:09,154
And you were wrong about me!

1112
01:19:09,238 --> 01:19:13,241
And I will never
let you use my hair again!

1113
01:19:13,326 --> 01:19:14,368
(GRUNTS)

1114
01:19:17,622 --> 01:19:19,164
(PANTING)

1115
01:19:22,418 --> 01:19:24,878
(SOFTLY) You want me
to be the bad guy?

1116
01:19:24,963 --> 01:19:28,799
Fine, now I'm the bad guy.

1117
01:19:31,052 --> 01:19:32,427
(GRUNTING)

1118
01:19:42,981 --> 01:19:44,564
What's this?

1119
01:19:44,649 --> 01:19:46,483
Open up!

1120
01:19:47,527 --> 01:19:49,569
- What's the password?
- What?

1121
01:19:49,654 --> 01:19:51,905
- (CHUCKLING) Nope.
- Open this door!

1122
01:19:51,990 --> 01:19:53,824
Not even close!

1123
01:19:53,992 --> 01:19:56,743
You have three seconds! One...

1124
01:19:57,662 --> 01:19:59,037
Two...

1125
01:20:00,957 --> 01:20:01,999
Three.

1126
01:20:03,876 --> 01:20:05,085
Huh?

1127
01:20:07,547 --> 01:20:09,715
Frying pans! Who knew, right?

1128
01:20:09,799 --> 01:20:11,341
(THUDDING)

1129
01:20:13,011 --> 01:20:14,511
(ALL YELLING)

1130
01:20:25,189 --> 01:20:27,441
(BELLOWING)

1131
01:20:27,525 --> 01:20:28,608
(ALL SCREAMING)

1132
01:20:33,031 --> 01:20:34,698
(PANTING)

1133
01:20:34,782 --> 01:20:35,991
(SOLDIERS YELLING)

1134
01:20:39,328 --> 01:20:40,620
- Head down.
- Head down.

1135
01:20:40,705 --> 01:20:41,788
- Arms in.
- Arms in.

1136
01:20:41,873 --> 01:20:43,540
- Knees apart.
- Knees apart. Knees apart?

1137
01:20:44,709 --> 01:20:46,501
Why do I need
to keep my knees apart...

1138
01:20:47,837 --> 01:20:51,131
(SCREAMING)

1139
01:20:52,133 --> 01:20:53,133
(EXHALES)

1140
01:20:53,217 --> 01:20:54,217
(NICKERS)

1141
01:20:54,719 --> 01:20:57,929
Max! You brought them here?

1142
01:21:00,141 --> 01:21:01,183
Thank you.

1143
01:21:01,309 --> 01:21:02,392
(NEIGHS)

1144
01:21:02,602 --> 01:21:05,228
No, really. Thank you.

1145
01:21:07,148 --> 01:21:08,482
I feel maybe this whole time,

1146
01:21:08,566 --> 01:21:10,484
we've just been misunderstanding
one another,

1147
01:21:10,568 --> 01:21:12,277
and we're really just...

1148
01:21:12,653 --> 01:21:13,945
You're right, we should go.

1149
01:21:19,285 --> 01:21:21,411
(SOLDIERS YELLING)

1150
01:21:21,579 --> 01:21:22,621
Max?

1151
01:21:23,748 --> 01:21:24,831
Max!

1152
01:21:25,458 --> 01:21:26,917
- Max!
- (NEIGHING)

1153
01:21:27,001 --> 01:21:30,128
(SCREAMING)

1154
01:21:31,672 --> 01:21:33,465
(NEIGHING)

1155
01:21:34,759 --> 01:21:35,759
(WOMAN EXCLAIMS)

1156
01:21:36,385 --> 01:21:39,554
Okay, Max.
Let's see how fast you can run.

1157
01:21:58,866 --> 01:22:00,033
Rapunzel?

1158
01:22:02,036 --> 01:22:03,620
Rapunzel, let down your hair!

1159
01:22:19,345 --> 01:22:21,721
Rapunzel,
I thought I'd never see you again.

1160
01:22:21,806 --> 01:22:22,848
Huh?

1161
01:22:22,974 --> 01:22:25,016
(SCREAMING MUFFLED WARNING)

1162
01:22:25,351 --> 01:22:26,852
- (GRUNTS)
- (GROANS)

1163
01:22:27,728 --> 01:22:28,728
(MUFFLED SCREAM)

1164
01:22:30,439 --> 01:22:33,358
Now look what you've done, Rapunzel.

1165
01:22:33,442 --> 01:22:37,779
Oh, don't worry, dear.
Our secret will die with him.

1166
01:22:37,864 --> 01:22:39,406
(MUFFLED PROTESTS)

1167
01:22:39,490 --> 01:22:41,116
GOTHEL: And as for us...

1168
01:22:41,284 --> 01:22:42,367
(SCOFFS)

1169
01:22:42,451 --> 01:22:47,080
We are going where no one
will ever find you again.

1170
01:22:47,248 --> 01:22:48,415
(MUFFLED SCREAMS)

1171
01:22:48,499 --> 01:22:49,499
(SNARLING)

1172
01:22:50,918 --> 01:22:53,044
- (GOTHEL GRUNTS)
- (SQUEAKS)

1173
01:22:53,129 --> 01:22:54,796
Rapunzel, really!

1174
01:22:55,631 --> 01:22:59,259
Enough already! Stop fighting me!

1175
01:22:59,886 --> 01:23:01,928
No! I won't stop!

1176
01:23:02,013 --> 01:23:05,223
For every minute of the rest of my life,
I will fight!

1177
01:23:05,308 --> 01:23:09,186
I will never stop trying
to get away from you!

1178
01:23:09,395 --> 01:23:10,687
(PANTING)

1179
01:23:11,606 --> 01:23:16,151
But if you let me save him,
I will go with you.

1180
01:23:16,903 --> 01:23:19,863
(GRUNTING) No! No, Rapunzel.

1181
01:23:20,740 --> 01:23:23,992
I'll never run. I'll never try to escape.

1182
01:23:24,076 --> 01:23:27,662
Just let me heal him
and you and I will be together,

1183
01:23:27,747 --> 01:23:29,789
forever, just like you want.

1184
01:23:29,874 --> 01:23:31,875
Everything will be the way it was.

1185
01:23:33,211 --> 01:23:34,336
I promise.

1186
01:23:35,254 --> 01:23:37,047
Just like you want.

1187
01:23:40,051 --> 01:23:43,386
(ENUNCIATING) Just let me heal him.

1188
01:23:48,935 --> 01:23:52,312
In case you get any ideas
about following us.

1189
01:23:52,396 --> 01:23:54,064
(COUGHING)

1190
01:23:54,398 --> 01:23:55,607
Eugene!

1191
01:23:55,900 --> 01:23:56,942
(COUGHING)

1192
01:23:57,026 --> 01:23:58,401
(GROANING)

1193
01:24:02,531 --> 01:24:04,950
I'm so sorry.
Everything is going to be okay, though.

1194
01:24:05,034 --> 01:24:06,034
No, Rapunzel.

1195
01:24:06,118 --> 01:24:09,496
I promise. You have to trust me.
Come on. Just breathe.

1196
01:24:09,580 --> 01:24:11,248
I can't let you do this.

1197
01:24:11,916 --> 01:24:14,042
And I can't let you die.

1198
01:24:14,585 --> 01:24:18,255
But if you do then you will die.

1199
01:24:18,339 --> 01:24:22,050
Hey. It's going to be all right.

1200
01:24:27,265 --> 01:24:28,431
(WEAKLY) Rapunzel.

1201
01:24:29,350 --> 01:24:30,475
Wait.

1202
01:24:39,402 --> 01:24:40,652
Eugene...

1203
01:24:41,612 --> 01:24:42,779
No!

1204
01:24:47,702 --> 01:24:48,952
(BLUBBERING)

1205
01:24:49,620 --> 01:24:50,620
(SHRIEKS)

1206
01:24:50,955 --> 01:24:54,582
What have you done?
What have you done?

1207
01:24:55,835 --> 01:24:56,960
No!

1208
01:25:00,548 --> 01:25:02,799
No! No. No!

1209
01:25:03,134 --> 01:25:07,429
(SOBBING)

1210
01:25:10,391 --> 01:25:11,641
(EXCLAIMING)

1211
01:25:12,643 --> 01:25:15,812
(SCREAMING)

1212
01:25:28,326 --> 01:25:31,077
(PANTING)

1213
01:25:31,329 --> 01:25:32,662
(GASPS)

1214
01:25:33,497 --> 01:25:35,373
No, no, no. Eugene.

1215
01:25:36,834 --> 01:25:38,043
(COUGHS)

1216
01:25:38,127 --> 01:25:42,505
No! Look at me. I'm right here.
Don't go. Stay with me.

1217
01:25:43,090 --> 01:25:46,176
(SINGING) Flower, gleam and glow
<i>Let your power shine</i>

1218
01:25:46,260 --> 01:25:49,179
<i>Make the clock reverse</i>
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

1219
01:25:49,263 --> 01:25:50,347
Rapunzel.

1220
01:25:50,765 --> 01:25:51,848
What?

1221
01:25:55,519 --> 01:25:57,395
(WEAKLY) You were my new dream.

1222
01:25:58,356 --> 01:25:59,647
(CHUCKLES SADLY)

1223
01:26:00,691 --> 01:26:02,442
And you were mine.

1224
01:26:07,448 --> 01:26:08,615
(EXHALES)

1225
01:26:28,803 --> 01:26:32,305
(SINGING) Heal what has been hurt

1226
01:26:33,724 --> 01:26:37,352
<i>Change the Fates' design</i>

1227
01:26:38,396 --> 01:26:41,481
<i>Save what has been lost</i>

1228
01:26:44,110 --> 01:26:46,945
<i>Bring back what once was mine</i>

1229
01:26:50,408 --> 01:26:52,367
<i>What once was mine</i>

1230
01:26:54,578 --> 01:26:57,455
(SOBBING)

1231
01:27:47,965 --> 01:27:49,215
(EXHALES)

1232
01:27:49,842 --> 01:27:51,301
Rapunzel?

1233
01:27:51,427 --> 01:27:53,678
(GASPS) Eugene?

1234
01:27:55,723 --> 01:27:58,683
Did I ever tell you
I've got a thing for brunettes?

1235
01:27:58,976 --> 01:28:00,268
(LAUGHS)

1236
01:28:00,895 --> 01:28:02,061
Eugene!

1237
01:28:02,146 --> 01:28:03,396
(LAUGHING)

1238
01:28:05,149 --> 01:28:06,983
(CRYING)

1239
01:29:23,310 --> 01:29:24,852
(LAUGHING SOFTLY)

1240
01:29:40,244 --> 01:29:41,244
(GASPS)

1241
01:29:41,620 --> 01:29:44,914
<i>FLYNN: Well, you can imagine</i>
<i>what happened next.</i>

1242
01:29:47,376 --> 01:29:50,962
<i>The kingdom rejoiced,</i>
<i>for their lost princess had returned.</i>

1243
01:29:51,046 --> 01:29:55,758
<i>The party lasted an entire week, and</i>
<i>honestly I don't remember most of it.</i>

1244
01:29:56,594 --> 01:29:58,386
<i>Dreams came true all over the place.</i>

1245
01:29:58,470 --> 01:30:01,764
<i>That guy went on to become the most</i>
<i>famous concert pianist in the world,</i>

1246
01:30:01,849 --> 01:30:03,516
<i>if you can believe it!</i>

1247
01:30:05,102 --> 01:30:08,479
<i>And this guy?</i>
<i>He eventually found true love.</i>

1248
01:30:09,440 --> 01:30:13,610
<i>As for this guy, I assume he's happy.</i>
<i>He's never told me otherwise.</i>

1249
01:30:14,778 --> 01:30:15,737
(NEIGHS SHARPLY)

1250
01:30:15,821 --> 01:30:16,904
<i>Thanks to Maximus,</i>

1251
01:30:16,989 --> 01:30:20,074
<i>crime in the kingdom</i>
<i>disappeared almost overnight.</i>

1252
01:30:20,200 --> 01:30:21,367
(GRUNTS)

1253
01:30:21,619 --> 01:30:23,661
<i>As did most of the apples.</i>

1254
01:30:25,414 --> 01:30:28,291
<i>Pascal never changed.</i>

1255
01:30:32,379 --> 01:30:36,382
<i>At last Rapunzel was home.</i>
<i>And she finally had a real family.</i>

1256
01:30:38,135 --> 01:30:40,720
<i>She was a princess worth waiting for.</i>

1257
01:30:40,804 --> 01:30:44,265
<i>Beloved by all, she led her kingdom</i>
<i>with all the grace and wisdom</i>

1258
01:30:44,350 --> 01:30:45,808
<i>that her parents did before her.</i>

1259
01:30:47,144 --> 01:30:50,271
<i>And, as for me,</i>
<i>I started going by Eugene again,</i>

1260
01:30:50,356 --> 01:30:52,482
<i>stopped thieving</i>
<i>and turned it all around.</i>

1261
01:30:52,566 --> 01:30:55,109
<i>But I know what the big question is.</i>

1262
01:30:55,194 --> 01:30:57,362
<i>Did Rapunzel and I ever get married?</i>

1263
01:30:57,446 --> 01:30:58,571
<i>I'm pleased to tell you</i>

1264
01:30:58,656 --> 01:31:03,034
<i>that after years and years</i>
<i>of asking and asking and asking...</i>

1265
01:31:05,162 --> 01:31:07,038
<i>I finally said yes.</i>

1266
01:31:07,122 --> 01:31:11,417
RAPUNZEL: (SCOLDING) Eugene.
<i>FLYNN: All right, I asked her.</i>

1267
01:31:11,502 --> 01:31:13,961
RAPUNZEL: And we're living
<i>happily ever after.</i>

1268
01:31:14,630 --> 01:31:28,059
FLYNN: Yes, we are.

1269
